    <i> FROM VIEWERS LIKE YOU.</i>     

23
00:01:18,779 --> 00:01:20,879
            Elyse:              
       <i> OUR FIRST STORY</i>         
    <i> INVESTIGATES A WEAPON</i>      

24
00:01:20,948 --> 00:01:22,414
   <i> THAT MAY HAVE BEEN FIRED</i>    

25
00:01:22,483 --> 00:01:25,651
    <i> IN ONE OF THE NATION'S</i>     
    <i> MOST INFAMOUS CRIMES.</i>      

26
00:01:25,719 --> 00:01:29,755
      <i> FEBRUARY 14, 1929,</i>       
     <i> ST. VALENTINE'S DAY:</i>      

27
00:01:29,824 --> 00:01:32,357
     <i> GANGSTERS TURN A DAY</i>      
    <i> OF LOVE AND REFLECTION</i>     

28
00:01:32,426 --> 00:01:33,859
      <i> INTO A BLOODBATH,</i>        

29
00:01:33,928 --> 00:01:36,662
     <i> EXECUTING SEVEN MEN</i>       
     <i> IN A CHICAGO GARAGE.</i>      

30
00:01:36,730 --> 00:01:38,463
    [ machine gun firing ]      

31
00:01:38,532 --> 00:01:41,934
 <i> AUTHORITIES SUSPECT THE HAND</i>  
<i> OF POWERFUL GANGSTER AL CAPONE,</i>

32
00:01:42,002 --> 00:01:45,938
<i> WHO WAS FIGHTING TO CONTROL THE</i>
 <i> CITY'S ILLEGAL LIQUOR TRADE.</i>  

33
00:01:46,006 --> 00:01:48,440
     <i> THE DAYLIGHT KILLING</i>      
     <i> OUTRAGES THE NATION</i>       

34
00:01:48,509 --> 00:01:51,710
     <i> AND BECOMES A SYMBOL</i>      
<i> OF THE FAILURE OF PROHIBITION.</i> 

35
00:01:51,779 --> 00:01:55,080
   <i> HOWEVER, NO ONE IS EVER</i>     
   <i> CONVICTED OF THE KILLING</i>    

36
00:01:55,149 --> 00:01:57,983
        <i> AND THE CRIME</i>          
      <i> REMAINS UNSOLVED.</i>        

37
00:01:58,052 --> 00:02:00,919
         <i> NOW MIKE LUX</i>          
  <i> OF LAKE GENEVA, WISCONSIN,</i>   

38
00:02:00,988 --> 00:02:03,021
       <i> BELIEVES HE HAS</i>         
      <i> THE MISSING WEAPON</i>       

39
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:05,857
     <i> FROM THIS LEGENDARY</i>       
      <i> GANGLAND MASSACRE.</i>       

40
00:02:05,926 --> 00:02:10,662
    THIS GUN MAY HAVE TAKEN     
     THE LIVES OF TWO MEN.      

41
00:02:10,731 --> 00:02:13,966
  <i> I'M ON MY WAY TO MEET MIKE</i>   
  <i> AND LOOK INTO HIS STORY. </i>    

42
00:02:14,034 --> 00:02:15,434
VERY NICE TO MEET YOU.          

43
00:02:18,739 --> 00:02:19,838
                        OH, WOW!

44
00:02:19,907 --> 00:02:21,306
12-GAUGE SHOTGUN.               

45
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:22,975
        LET'S TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

46
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:24,610
 AND WHAT'S THE STORY BEHIND IT?

47
00:02:24,678 --> 00:02:28,146
IT WAS SUPPOSEDLY USED IN THE   
ST. VALENTINE'S DAY MASSACRE.   

48
00:02:28,215 --> 00:02:29,982
             THAT WAS IN CHICAGO
             IN 1929.           

49
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:31,116
YES.                            

50
00:02:31,185 --> 00:02:32,751
       YOU KNOW, JUST BY LOOKING
       AT THE GUN,              

51
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:35,153
          TO ME IT KIND OF LOOKS
          LIKE THE BARREL       

52
00:02:35,222 --> 00:02:36,855
     IS NOT PERIOD TO THE PIECE.

53
00:02:36,924 --> 00:02:38,223
CORRECT.                        

54
00:02:38,292 --> 00:02:41,226
I HAD THIS BARREL PUT ON        
TO MAKE IT LEGAL.               

55
00:02:41,295 --> 00:02:45,230
ORIGINALLY THE BARREL WAS CUT   
OFF PROBABLY ABOUT RIGHT HERE.  

56
00:02:45,299 --> 00:02:48,400
AND I ACTUALLY HAVE             
A COUPLE PICTURES OF IT.        

57
00:02:48,469 --> 00:02:50,602
      OH, AND I CAN SEE         
      THE BARREL'S MUCH SHORTER.

58
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:53,038
      <i> MIKE TELLS ME THAT</i>       
    <i> SHORT-BARREL SHOTGUNS</i>      

59
00:02:53,107 --> 00:02:54,773
   <i> ARE FEDERALLY REGULATED</i>     

60
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:56,775
<i> AND THAT HE PUT A LONGER BARREL</i>
          <i> ON THE GUN</i>           

61
00:02:56,844 --> 00:02:58,310
 <i> TO COMPLY WITH THESE RULES.</i>   

62
00:02:58,379 --> 00:02:59,711
          HOW'D YOU GET THE GUN?

63
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:01,913
I HAD INHERITED IT FROM         
MY FATHER WHEN HE PASSED AWAY.  

64
00:03:01,982 --> 00:03:03,715
     <i> MIKE SAYS HIS FATHER</i>      
         <i> GOT THE GUN</i>           

65
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:06,818
  <i> FROM A FORMER CHICAGO FIRE</i>   
 <i> COMMISSIONER, ROBERT QUINN.</i>   

66
00:03:06,887 --> 00:03:09,655
  <i> MIKE BELIEVES THAT QUINN,</i>    
     <i> WHO IS NOW DECEASED,</i>      

67
00:03:09,723 --> 00:03:13,225
 <i> MAY HAVE USED HIS INFLUENCE</i>   
<i> TO SECRETLY ACQUIRE THE GUN. </i>  

68
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:15,293
I THINK WHEN QUINN              
ACQUIRED IT,                    

69
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:17,963
IT HAD TO HAVE BEEN             
IN THE MID-'70s.                

70
00:03:18,032 --> 00:03:21,299
   <i> MIKE'S FATHER WAS KILLED</i>    
   <i> IN AN AIR CRASH IN 1979.</i>    

71
00:03:21,368 --> 00:03:24,069
TWO DAYS LATER, ONE OF          
HIS FRIENDS TALKED TO ME,       

72
00:03:24,138 --> 00:03:28,040
AND HE WAS VERY UPSET           
ABOUT THE PLANE CRASH,          

73
00:03:28,108 --> 00:03:32,544
BUT HE WAS ALSO VERY WORRIED    
THAT NOW I OWN THIS PIECE       

74
00:03:32,613 --> 00:03:35,881
AND HE DIDN'T WANT ME           
TO BE SHOWING IT OFF            

75
00:03:35,949 --> 00:03:40,619
OR TELLING ANYBODY ABOUT IT,    
AND I HAVEN'T.                  

76
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:44,823
THAT'S WHY I'VE HAD IT          
FOR 30 YEARS HIDDEN AWAY.       

77
00:03:44,892 --> 00:03:47,159
  WHAT'D YOU THINK WHEN YOUR DAD
  TOLD YOU THAT THIS WAS USED   

78
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:48,960
      IN THE ST. VALENTINE'S DAY
      MASSACRE?                 

79
00:03:49,029 --> 00:03:51,897
I THOUGHT, "COME ON,            
YOU'RE PULLING MY LEG."         

80
00:03:51,965 --> 00:03:53,999
AND HE WAS DEAD SERIOUS.        

81
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:56,501
AND HE WAS A SERIOUS            
KIND OF GUY.                    

82
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:59,337
WHEN IT CAME TO WEAPONS         
LIKE THIS IN HIS COLLECTION,    

83
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,939
HE WAS NOT FOOLING.             

84
00:04:01,008 --> 00:04:02,707
            MIKE, WHAT EXACTLY  
            DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?

85
00:04:02,776 --> 00:04:06,144
IF IT TRULY IS THE SHOTGUN      
THAT WAS USED                   

86
00:04:06,213 --> 00:04:08,213
AT THE ST. VALENTINE'S DAY      
MASSACRE.                       

87
00:04:08,282 --> 00:04:09,614
           I WILL SEE WHAT I CAN
           FIND OUT.            

88
00:04:09,683 --> 00:04:11,650
    DO YOU MIND IF I SIT HERE   
    FOR A WHILE AND EVALUATE IT?

89
00:04:11,718 --> 00:04:13,618
ABSOLUTELY NOT.                 

90
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:15,821
   I USED TO WORK IN THE GUN    
   DEPARTMENT AT CHRISTIE'S,    

91
00:04:15,889 --> 00:04:17,823
    SO I KNOW A LITTLE BIT      
          ABOUT GUNS.           

92
00:04:17,891 --> 00:04:19,958
      AND THE FIRST THING       
      I NEED TO DETERMINE       

93
00:04:20,027 --> 00:04:23,361
        WAS IF THIS GUN         
   WAS EVEN AROUND IN 1929.     

94
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:25,630
   WAS IT PERIOD TO THE TIME    
       OF THE MASSACRE?         

95
00:04:25,699 --> 00:04:27,399
 <i> IT CERTAINLY APPEARS TO BE.</i>   

96
00:04:27,468 --> 00:04:29,367
     <i> THE WOODEN FORESTOCK</i>      
     <i> IS FOR A REPEATING,</i>       

97
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:31,336
       <i> OR PUMP-ACTION,</i>         
           <i> SHOTGUN.</i>            

98
00:04:31,405 --> 00:04:33,171
    <i> THAT MEANS IT CAN FIRE</i>     
        <i> MULTIPLE SHOTS</i>         

99
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,940
      <i> WITHOUT RELOADING.</i>       

100
00:04:35,008 --> 00:04:36,975
     I KNOW THAT THERE IS       
     A SERIAL NUMBER HERE.      

101
00:04:37,044 --> 00:04:42,414
        AH, HERE IT IS:         
           18514 B.             

102
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:44,749
       <i> THAT MAY HELP US</i>        
 <i> MORE PRECISELY DATE THE GUN,</i>  

103
00:04:44,818 --> 00:04:47,719
      <i> ALTHOUGH BACK THEN</i>       
<i> I'M PRETTY CERTAIN A PURCHASER</i> 

104
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:50,088
       <i> WAS NOT REQUIRED</i>        
  <i> TO REGISTER THEIR WEAPON.</i>    

105
00:04:50,157 --> 00:04:53,225
      I SEE THAT IT SAYS        
 "WESTERN FIELD" ON THE PLATE.  

106
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:56,795
YOU KNOW, I DID NOTICE SOMETHING
UNUSUAL OVER HERE ON THE STOCK. 

107
00:04:56,864 --> 00:04:58,563
    THERE ARE TWO NOTCHES.      

108
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:01,066
    MAYBE WE COULD GET SOME     
INFORMATION FROM THAT AS WELL.  

109
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:02,968
 <i> IF THIS GUN REALLY WAS USED</i>   

110
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:05,070
  <i> IN THE ST. VALENTINE'S DAY</i>   
          <i> MASSACRE,</i>            

111
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:07,105
<i> THEN IT'S AN EXCEPTIONAL PIECE</i> 
          <i> OF HISTORY</i>           

112
00:05:07,174 --> 00:05:09,941
   <i> AND ITS COLLECTION VALUE</i>    
     <i> WOULD BE VERY HIGH.</i>       

113
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:13,545
        <i> ON THE MORNING</i>         
    <i> OF FEBRUARY 14, 1929,</i>      

114
00:05:13,614 --> 00:05:16,715
<i> SEVEN IMMACULATELY DRESSED MEN</i> 
     <i> GATHERED IN A GARAGE</i>      

115
00:05:16,783 --> 00:05:19,084
   <i> ON CHICAGO'S NORTH SIDE.</i>    

116
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:20,719
      <i> SOME WERE MEMBERS</i>        
          <i> OF A GANG</i>            

117
00:05:20,787 --> 00:05:23,488
<i> LED BY THE NOTORIOUS BOOTLEGGER</i>
         <i> BUGS MORAN.</i>           

118
00:05:23,557 --> 00:05:25,824
       <i> WITHOUT WARNING,</i>        
      <i> GUNMEN STORMED IN</i>        

119
00:05:25,892 --> 00:05:29,628
<i> AND UNLEASHED A HAIL OF BULLETS</i>
  <i> THAT LEFT ALL SEVEN DEAD.</i>    

120
00:05:29,696 --> 00:05:31,263
  <i> WITNESSES REPORTED SEEING</i>    

121
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:34,165
 <i> WHAT LOOKED LIKE TWO POLICE</i>   
  <i> OFFICERS LEAVE THE GARAGE.</i>   

122
00:05:34,234 --> 00:05:36,968
  <i> THE MID-MORNING SLAUGHTER</i>    
  <i> TURNED THE MEDIA SPOTLIGHT</i>   

123
00:05:37,037 --> 00:05:40,038
<i> ON THE CITY OF CHICAGO AND THE</i> 
 <i> VIOLENT STRUGGLE BEING WAGED</i>  

124
00:05:40,107 --> 00:05:43,008
         <i> OVER CONTROL</i>          
 <i> OF THE ILLEGAL LIQUOR TRADE.</i>  

125
00:05:46,413 --> 00:05:48,947
    <i> I'M IN CHICAGO TO MEET</i>     
   <i> THE AUTHOR OF THIS BOOK,</i>    

126
00:05:49,016 --> 00:05:50,482
          <i> ART BILEK.</i>           

127
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:54,753
                  HI, ART.      

128
00:05:54,821 --> 00:05:56,788
HERE IS THE GUN.                

129
00:05:56,857 --> 00:05:58,256
TELL ME YOUR OPINION ON THAT.   

130
00:05:58,325 --> 00:05:59,758
WHAT DO I HAVE HERE?            

131
00:05:59,826 --> 00:06:01,359
      IT'S A 12-GAUGE SHOTGUN...

132
00:06:01,428 --> 00:06:03,228
         <i> ART IS ALSO</i>           
   <i> A FORMER POLICE OFFICER</i>     

133
00:06:03,297 --> 00:06:06,765
<i> AND FAMILIAR WITH THE WEAPONS</i>  
   <i> OF CHOICE OF CRIMINALS.</i>     

134
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:10,168
       MOST IMPORTANTLY,        
       IT HAS A SAWED-OFF STOCK.

135
00:06:10,237 --> 00:06:15,206
       GANGSTERS IN THE 1920s   
       HAD THESE STOCKS MODIFIED

136
00:06:15,275 --> 00:06:19,511
SO THAT THEY COULD CARRY THESE  
UNDER THEIR OVERCOATS LIKE THIS.

137
00:06:19,579 --> 00:06:20,779
SO IT'S A GANGSTER GUN?         

138
00:06:20,847 --> 00:06:22,347
                        OH, YES.

139
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:24,482
 IN FACT, THAT'S THE WAY I WOULD
 REFER TO IT, AS A GANGSTER GUN.

140
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:26,184
     <i> ART SAYS EXACTLY HOW</i>      
         <i> THE VICTIMS</i>           

141
00:06:26,253 --> 00:06:28,620
  <i> WERE LURED TO THEIR DEATH</i>    
    <i> WAS NEVER ESTABLISHED.</i>     

142
00:06:28,689 --> 00:06:31,322
   <i> INVESTIGATORS SUSPECTED</i>     
     <i> THE PHONY POLICEMEN</i>       

143
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,158
 <i> WERE AL CAPONE GANG MEMBERS.</i>  

144
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:34,993
      <i> WHEN THEY ORDERED</i>        
     <i> THE RIVAL GANGSTERS</i>       

145
00:06:35,062 --> 00:06:36,528
 <i> TO LINE UP AND TURN AROUND,</i>   

146
00:06:36,596 --> 00:06:39,164
   <i> MORE CAPONE MEN ENTERED,</i>    
      <i> CARRYING WEAPONS.</i>        

147
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,199
           WE DON'T KNOW EXACTLY
           WHAT WENT ON         

148
00:06:41,268 --> 00:06:44,669
EXCEPT TWO OF THE MEN PULLED OUT
THOMPSON SUBMACHINE GUNS        

149
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:48,173
     AND BEGAN RIDDLING THE BACK
     OF THESE SEVEN MEN         

150
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:49,841
       WITH MACHINE GUN BULLETS.

151
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:52,844
<i> GETTING INFORMATION ABOUT THE</i>  
 <i> CRIME WAS ALMOST IMPOSSIBLE.</i>  

152
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:55,580
    <i> THE CHICAGO UNDERWORLD</i>     
      <i> WAS RULED BY FEAR.</i>       

153
00:06:55,649 --> 00:06:58,283
     <i> BEFORE DYING, ONE OF</i>      
<i> THE VICTIMS, FRANK GUSENBERG,</i>  

154
00:06:58,351 --> 00:07:01,519
   <i> TOLD INCREDULOUS POLICE,</i>    
      <i> "NOBODY SHOT ME."</i>        

155
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:03,288
     <i> INVESTIGATORS TURNED</i>      
         <i> TO EVIDENCE</i>           

156
00:07:03,356 --> 00:07:05,090
<i> FROM THE BLOOD-DRENCHED GARAGE.</i>

157
00:07:05,158 --> 00:07:08,726
 SERGEANT JAMES LOFTUS, WHO WAS 
 THE FIRST OFFICER ON THE SCENE,

158
00:07:08,795 --> 00:07:12,797
        WAS ABLE TO COLLECT FROM
        THE SCENE SEVERAL ITEMS.

159
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:15,333
         HERE IS A COPY         
         OF THE INVENTORY REPORT

160
00:07:15,402 --> 00:07:17,569
    THAT HE FILED THAT VERY DAY.

161
00:07:17,637 --> 00:07:20,638
<i> THERE WERE SEVERAL .45-CALIBER</i> 
     <i> SHELLS AND BULLETS,</i>       

162
00:07:20,707 --> 00:07:24,309
 <i> THE SIZE OF AMMUNITION USED</i>   
      <i> IN THE TOMMY GUN.</i>        

163
00:07:24,377 --> 00:07:25,777
   <i> ART POINTS OUT SOMETHING</i>    
   <i> OF PARTICULAR INTEREST.</i>     

164
00:07:25,846 --> 00:07:27,412
           AND THERE IS THE ITEM
           RIGHT THERE:         

165
00:07:27,481 --> 00:07:30,014
   TWO SHOTGUN SHELLS, 12-GAUGE.

166
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,951
    <i> THAT'S THE SAME GAUGE</i>      
        <i> AS MIKE'S GUN.</i>         

167
00:07:33,019 --> 00:07:36,187
<i> I TELL ART THAT MIKE BELIEVES</i>  
   <i> HIS WEAPON ONCE BELONGED</i>    

168
00:07:36,256 --> 00:07:38,923
  <i> TO ROBERT QUINN, A FORMER</i>    
  <i> CHICAGO FIRE COMMISSIONER</i>    

169
00:07:38,992 --> 00:07:41,726
         <i> IN THE 1950s</i>          
      <i> THROUGH THE 1970s.</i>       

170
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:44,262
  HE WAS ONE OF THE MORE NOTABLE
  FIRE COMMISSIONERS            

171
00:07:44,331 --> 00:07:46,364
      IN THE HISTORY OF CHICAGO.

172
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:49,400
 <i> HE SAYS QUINN WAS PART OF AN</i>  
<i> INNER CIRCLE AROUND THE MAYOR</i>  

173
00:07:49,469 --> 00:07:51,703
         <i> IN A PERIOD</i>           
  <i> WHEN CONTROL OF EVIDENCE,</i>    

174
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:54,372
        <i> ESPECIALLY FOR</i>         
   <i> A CELEBRATED COLD CASE,</i>     

175
00:07:54,441 --> 00:07:57,175
        <i> WAS NOT NEARLY</i>         
  <i> AS TIGHTLY HELD AS TODAY.</i>    

176
00:07:57,244 --> 00:07:59,310
DO YOU THINK THAT HE COULD      
HAVE OWNED THIS GUN?            

177
00:07:59,379 --> 00:08:00,979
              HE KNEW ALL OF    
              THE TOP OFFICIALS.

178
00:08:01,047 --> 00:08:03,014
          HE WOULD HAVE KNOWN   
          THE CORONER VERY WELL.

179
00:08:03,083 --> 00:08:05,917
AND HE WOULD HAVE KNOWN OTHER   
PEOPLE IN THE POLICE DEPARTMENT.

180
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:09,420
         IT'S ENTIRELY POSSIBLE 
         THAT ONE WAY OR ANOTHER

181
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:12,724
HE MIGHT HAVE MET A MAN         
THAT HAD POSSESSION OF THIS GUN.

182
00:08:12,792 --> 00:08:14,893
   <i> ART SAYS THE DESCRIPTION</i>    
    <i> OF TWO OF THE KILLERS</i>      

183
00:08:14,961 --> 00:08:16,561
  <i> DRESSED IN POLICE UNIFORMS</i>   

184
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:18,630
      <i> TURNED UP THE HEAT</i>       
      <i> ON INVESTIGATORS,</i>        

185
00:08:18,698 --> 00:08:21,900
<i> BUT IT WASN'T UNTIL TEN MONTHS</i> 
<i> LATER THAT THEY CAUGHT A BREAK:</i>

186
00:08:21,968 --> 00:08:25,236
    <i> AN AL CAPONE ASSOCIATE</i>     
  <i> NAMED FRED "KILLER" BURKE</i>    

187
00:08:25,305 --> 00:08:29,307
<i> WAS INVOLVED IN A FENDER BENDER</i>
<i> ACROSS STATE LINES IN MICHIGAN.</i>

188
00:08:29,376 --> 00:08:31,342
WELL, THERE WAS A POLICE OFFICER
ON THE NEXT CORNER,             

189
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:33,278
      AND HE BEGAN WALKING DOWN.

190
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:36,281
         WITH THAT, KILLER BURKE
         DRIVES OFF,            

191
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:38,149
           THE POLICEMAN JUMPS  
           ON THE RUNNING BOARD,

192
00:08:38,218 --> 00:08:40,385
         BURKE TAKES OUT HIS GUN
         AND SHOOTS HIM.        

193
00:08:40,453 --> 00:08:42,553
             THE OFFICER TUMBLES
             TO THE GROUND DEAD.

194
00:08:42,622 --> 00:08:44,389
         A HUGE MANHUNT FOLLOWS,

195
00:08:44,457 --> 00:08:48,159
       AND THAT'S HOW THEY FOUND
       BURKE'S CAR OVERTURNED   

196
00:08:48,228 --> 00:08:51,529
  WHERE HE TRIED TO MAKE        
  A TURN IN THE ROAD AND FAILED.

197
00:08:51,598 --> 00:08:54,866
 <i> ART EXPLAINS THAT BURKE WAS</i>   
<i> A CAREER GANGSTER AND HIT MAN.</i> 

198
00:08:54,935 --> 00:08:57,969
  <i> A WORLD WAR I VET, HE WAS</i>    
   <i> SUSPECTED OF INTRODUCING</i>    

199
00:08:58,038 --> 00:09:00,838
 <i> THE THOMPSON SUBMACHINE GUN</i>   
     <i> TO THE DETROIT MOB,</i>       

200
00:09:00,907 --> 00:09:03,708
   <i> HELPING MURDER THREE MEN</i>    
           <i> IN 1927.</i>            

201
00:09:03,777 --> 00:09:07,211
   <i> IN THE AFTERMATH OF THE</i>     
<i> ST. VALENTINE'S DAY KILLINGS,</i>  

202
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:09,580
      <i> BURKE WAS HOLED UP</i>       
  <i> IN A SMALL MICHIGAN TOWN.</i>    

203
00:09:09,649 --> 00:09:13,017
  <i> AFTER KILLING THE OFFICER,</i>   
  <i> POLICE RAIDED HIS HIDEOUT.</i>   

204
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:16,621
     AND UPSTAIRS ON THE SECOND 
     FLOOR, THEY OPENED A CLOSET

205
00:09:16,690 --> 00:09:19,724
        AND THERE WERE THE TWO  
        MACHINE GUNS, A SHOTGUN,

206
00:09:19,793 --> 00:09:22,493
            AND SOME OTHER      
            ARMORY-TYPE DEVICES.

207
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,562
      <i> FORENSIC ANALYSIS</i>        
     <i> WOULD LATER CONNECT</i>       

208
00:09:24,631 --> 00:09:26,998
 <i> SOME OF FRED BURKE'S WEAPONS</i>  
       <i> TO THE MASSACRE.</i>        

209
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:28,599
WHERE ARE THOSE GUNS NOW?       

210
00:09:28,668 --> 00:09:31,102
    THE GUNS AT THE CURRENT TIME
    ARE BEING HELD              

211
00:09:31,171 --> 00:09:34,806
BY THE BERRIEN COUNTY, MICHIGAN,
SHERIFF'S OFFICE,               

212
00:09:34,874 --> 00:09:36,908
       WHERE THEY WERE RECOVERED
       IN THE FIRST PLACE.      

213
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:40,545
<i> I'M IN BERRIEN COUNTY TO MEET</i>  
 <i> WITH LIEUTENANT KEITH HAFER,</i>  

214
00:09:40,613 --> 00:09:44,782
 <i> THE WEAPONS EXPERT IN CHARGE</i>  
    <i> OF THE MASSACRE GUNS.</i>      

215
00:09:44,851 --> 00:09:46,317
        WOW.                    

216
00:09:46,386 --> 00:09:48,753
THESE ARE THE TWO THOMPSON      
SUBMACHINE GUNS USED            

217
00:09:48,822 --> 00:09:50,688
IN THE ST. VALENTINE'S DAY      
MASSACRE.                       

218
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:52,724
  <i> LIEUTENANT HAFER EXPLAINS</i>    
       <i> THAT FOR YEARS,</i>         

219
00:09:52,792 --> 00:09:54,459
      <i> THE GUNS WERE HELD</i>       
          <i> BY THE FBI</i>           

220
00:09:54,527 --> 00:09:57,495
<i> AT THEIR BALLISTICS CRIME LAB</i>  
    <i> IN QUANTICO, VIRGINIA.</i>     

221
00:09:57,564 --> 00:10:01,332
<i> IN THE LATE 1970s, A MICHIGAN</i>  
<i> DETECTIVE TRAINING WITH THE FBI</i>

222
00:10:01,401 --> 00:10:03,868
       <i> SPOTTED THE GUNS</i>        
 <i> AND ASKED FOR THEIR RETURN.</i>   

223
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:05,636
ARE THESE THE ONLY GUNS         
THAT YOU HAVE?                  

224
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:08,072
    THERE WERE OTHER GUNS SEIZED
    FROM FRED BURKE'S HOME,     

225
00:10:08,141 --> 00:10:11,075
   BUT THOSE GUNS ARE LONG GONE 
   AND I HAVE NO RECORD OF THEM.

226
00:10:11,144 --> 00:10:13,111
WELL, I'M INVESTIGATING         
THIS SHOTGUN                    

227
00:10:13,179 --> 00:10:15,079
THAT I BELIEVE MAY HAVE BEEN    
USED AT THE MASSACRE.           

228
00:10:15,148 --> 00:10:16,380
    IT'S CERTAINLY THE RIGHT AGE

229
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:17,882
               AND IT LOOKS LIKE
               A GANGSTER GUN.  

230
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:19,851
       WHAT I NOTICE IMMEDIATELY
       ARE THESE TWO NOTCHES    

231
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:22,386
        CUT INTO THE PISTOL GRIP
        OF THIS SHOTGUN.        

232
00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:24,088
    <i> LIEUTENANT HAFER SAYS</i>      

233
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:26,557
  <i> CRIMINALS SOMETIMES CARVED</i>   
   <i> NOTCHES ON THEIR WEAPONS</i>    

234
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:28,359
   <i> WHEN THEY KILLED A MAN.</i>     

235
00:10:28,428 --> 00:10:31,429
               AND THE THOMPSONS
               THAT WE HAVE     

236
00:10:31,498 --> 00:10:35,399
        HAVE NOTCHES CARVED     
        INTO THE TRIGGER GUARDS.

237
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,068
        <i> HE'S NOT SURE</i>          
       <i> IF THE MARKINGS</i>         

238
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:38,936
     <i> CAN CONNECT OUR GUN</i>       
       <i> TO THE MASSACRE,</i>        

239
00:10:39,005 --> 00:10:41,105
    <i> BUT OFFERS TO TAKE ME</i>      
     <i> TO THE FIRING RANGE</i>       

240
00:10:41,174 --> 00:10:44,008
 <i> TO SHOW EXACTLY WHY OUR GUN</i>   
      <i> AND THE TOMMY GUN</i>        

241
00:10:44,077 --> 00:10:46,210
   <i> WOULD HAVE BEEN FAVORITE</i>    
      <i> GANGSTER WEAPONS.</i>        

242
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:48,112
FIRE!                           

243
00:10:48,181 --> 00:10:50,815
HIT HIM RIGHT IN THE CHEST,     
KEEP GOING.                     

244
00:10:52,752 --> 00:10:55,153
        <i> THE TOMMY GUN</i>          
    <i> CAN FIRE CONTINUOUSLY.</i>     

245
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:58,289
<i> LIEUTENANT HAFER HAS TOLD ME TO</i>
<i> FIRE JUST THREE SHOTS AT A TIME</i>

246
00:10:58,358 --> 00:11:01,025
      <i> BECAUSE THE WEAPON</i>       
   <i> IS DIFFICULT TO CONTROL.</i>    

247
00:11:01,094 --> 00:11:02,426
    IT'S PRETTY POWERFUL.       

248
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:04,695
    <i> LIEUTENANT HAFER SAYS</i>      
     <i> THIS MODEL TOMMY GUN</i>      

249
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:08,366
  <i> COULD UNLOAD A DEVASTATING</i>   
     <i> 700 ROUNDS A MINUTE.</i>      

250
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:10,668
I CAN UNDERSTAND WHY            
A GANGSTER LIKES THAT GUN.      

251
00:11:10,737 --> 00:11:13,004
     IT WAS THE HIGH-TECH WEAPON
     OF ITS DAY.                

252
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:15,873
 <i> HE TELLS ME THAT BEFORE THE</i>   
<i> INTRODUCTION OF THE TOMMY GUN</i>  

253
00:11:15,942 --> 00:11:18,609
  <i> TO THE CHICAGO CRIME WORLD</i>   
           <i> IN 1924,</i>            

254
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:22,580
  <i> THE REPEATING SHOTGUN WAS</i>    
 <i> THE GANGSTER GUN OF CHOICE. </i>  

255
00:11:22,649 --> 00:11:25,950
WHAT YOU HAVE HERE IS           
A PUMP-ACTION REPEATING SHOTGUN,

256
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:29,554
 WHICH WAS A VERY COMMON AND    
 DEVASTATING WEAPON OF THE TIME.

257
00:11:29,622 --> 00:11:33,124
 <i> OUR GUN IS CAPABLE OF FIRING</i>  
 <i> SIX SHOTS BEFORE RELOADING,</i>   

258
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:36,694
<i> UNLEASHING A DEVASTATING SPRAY</i> 
     <i> OF SHOTGUN PELLETS.</i>       

259
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:43,301
     WOULD YOU LIKE TO SHOOT IT?

260
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,368
YEAH, DEFINITELY.               

261
00:11:44,437 --> 00:11:46,003
               PULL IT IN TIGHT,
               YEP.             

262
00:11:46,072 --> 00:11:48,239
           AIM AT YOUR TARGET   
           AND SHOOT WHEN READY.

263
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:53,110
  [ gunshots and reloading ]    

264
00:11:53,179 --> 00:11:55,212
           WOW, THAT'S GOT QUITE
           A KICK TO IT.        

265
00:11:55,281 --> 00:11:57,181
WHY DON'T YOU OPEN THE BOLT     
AND LET'S MAKE SURE IT'S EMPTY. 

266
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,416
                 OKAY.          

267
00:11:58,484 --> 00:11:59,850
          NOW, DO YOU THINK     
          THAT THIS GUN WAS USED

268
00:11:59,919 --> 00:12:01,385
  IN THE ST. VALENTINE MASSACRE?

269
00:12:01,454 --> 00:12:03,054
IT'S CERTAINLY A POSSIBILITY.   

270
00:12:03,122 --> 00:12:05,790
  <i> LIEUTENANT HAFER SUGGESTS</i>    
 <i> I PICK UP THE SHELL CASINGS.</i>  

271
00:12:05,858 --> 00:12:08,192
     <i> IF OUR GUN WAS USED</i>       
       <i> IN THE MASSACRE,</i>        

272
00:12:08,261 --> 00:12:12,430
     <i> THE SHELLS MAY BEAR</i>       
 <i> USEFUL FORENSIC INFORMATION.</i>  

273
00:12:12,498 --> 00:12:16,000
  <i> HE'S NOT SURE WHAT REMAINS</i>   
   <i> IN THE OLD POLICE FILES</i>     

274
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:18,602
  <i> BUT SUGGESTS I SPEAK WITH</i>    
 <i> POLICE HISTORIAN CHRISS LYON</i>  

275
00:12:18,671 --> 00:12:21,605
  <i> AT THE HERITAGE MUSEUM AND</i>   
<i> CULTURAL CENTER IN ST. JOSEPH.</i> 

276
00:12:21,674 --> 00:12:23,140
                     HI, CHRISS.
HI, ELYSE.                      

277
00:12:23,209 --> 00:12:24,709
GREAT TO MEET YOU,              
WELCOME TO ST. JOSEPH, MICHIGAN.

278
00:12:24,777 --> 00:12:26,243
                      THANK YOU.

279
00:12:26,312 --> 00:12:29,380
<i> CHRISS SAYS THE POLICE FOUND A</i> 
<i> TROVE OF INCRIMINATING EVIDENCE</i>

280
00:12:29,449 --> 00:12:31,716
       <i> WHEN THEY RAIDED</i>        
    <i> FRED BURKE'S HIDEOUT.</i>      

281
00:12:31,784 --> 00:12:34,118
          THIS ONE IS ONE       
          OF THE ORIGINAL PHOTOS

282
00:12:34,187 --> 00:12:37,154
         OF SOME OF THE WEAPONRY
         THAT WAS FOUND         

283
00:12:37,223 --> 00:12:38,789
          IN FRED BURKE'S HOUSE.

284
00:12:38,858 --> 00:12:40,725
OKAY, SO I SEE HERE             
THE TWO TOMMY GUNS              

285
00:12:40,793 --> 00:12:42,126
THAT WERE FOUND IN HIS HOUSE.   

286
00:12:42,195 --> 00:12:43,794
AND THIS IS ALL THE ARSENAL.    

287
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:45,529
AND THIS MUST BE THE SHOTGUN.   

288
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:47,965
<i> CHRISS EXPLAINS HOW THE CHICAGO</i>
    <i> AUTHORITIES HAD TURNED</i>     

289
00:12:48,034 --> 00:12:50,501
    <i> TO A FORENSICS EXPERT</i>      
     <i> NAMED CALVIN GODDARD</i>      

290
00:12:50,570 --> 00:12:52,269
<i> TO EXAMINE THE BURKE WEAPONS.</i>  

291
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:55,406
    WHEN GODDARD TOOK THESE GUNS
    TO BE TESTED BALLISTICALLY, 

292
00:12:55,475 --> 00:12:58,609
          HE TOOK THE TOMMY GUNS
          AND HE TOOK THIS GUN, 

293
00:12:58,678 --> 00:13:00,478
            WHICH IS A 20-GAUGE.

294
00:13:00,546 --> 00:13:03,114
         NOW, WE KNOW THAT THERE
         WAS A 12-GAUGE USED    

295
00:13:03,182 --> 00:13:04,749
      IN THE ST. VALENTINE'S DAY
      MASSACRE                  

296
00:13:04,817 --> 00:13:06,050
  BY THE SHELLS THAT WERE FOUND.

297
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:08,219
SO IF THIS GUN WASN'T USED      
IN THE MASSACRE,                

298
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:10,788
THEN IT'S STILL POSSIBLE        
THAT OUR GUN WAS.               

299
00:13:10,857 --> 00:13:14,291
<i> I'M CURIOUS, HAD GODDARD ALSO</i>  
 <i> EXAMINED THE 12-GAUGE SHELLS</i>  

300
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:17,995
   <i> FOUND AT THE CRIME SCENE</i>    
     <i> AFTER THE MASSACRE?</i>       

301
00:13:18,064 --> 00:13:20,998
       <i> CHRISS SUGGESTS</i>         
         <i> I SPEAK WITH</i>          

302
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:23,367
  <i> FORMER CRIME LAB DIRECTOR</i>    
       <i> PAUL DOUGHERTY,</i>         

303
00:13:23,436 --> 00:13:24,869
 <i> WHO HAS STUDIED THE MASSACRE</i>  

304
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:26,604
      <i> AND THE SUBSEQUENT</i>       
    <i> POLICE DETECTIVE WORK.</i>     

305
00:13:26,672 --> 00:13:28,172
         OKAY, SO HERE'S THE GUN
         I TALKED TO YOU ABOUT. 

306
00:13:28,241 --> 00:13:29,607
YES.                            
              WHAT DO YOU THINK?

307
00:13:29,675 --> 00:13:32,710
THIS IS A WESTERN FIELD,        
WHICH IS MADE BY STEVENS.       

308
00:13:32,779 --> 00:13:34,879
IT HAS A FAIRLY LOW             
SERIAL NUMBER,                  

309
00:13:34,947 --> 00:13:36,881
WHICH INDICATES                 
IT'S FAIRLY OLD.                

310
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:41,452
  <i> PAUL SAYS THE MODEL WAS IN</i>   
 <i> PRODUCTION FROM 1905 TO 1932</i>  

311
00:13:41,521 --> 00:13:43,187
 <i> AND PERIOD TO THE MASSACRE.</i>   

312
00:13:43,256 --> 00:13:45,723
 <i> HOWEVER, HE CAN'T PRECISELY</i>   
         <i> DATE THE GUN</i>          

313
00:13:45,792 --> 00:13:48,092
  <i> BECAUSE THE MANUFACTURER'S</i>   
        <i> SERIAL RECORDS</i>         

314
00:13:48,161 --> 00:13:49,527
     <i> HAVE BEEN DESTROYED.</i>      

315
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:51,028
         SO TELL ME A LITTLE BIT
         ABOUT GODDARD.         

316
00:13:51,097 --> 00:13:53,831
WELL, CALVIN GODDARD            
WAS A FIRST-CLASS SCIENTIST     

317
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:57,468
AND HE APPROACHED EVERYTHING    
THAT HE DID AS A SCIENTIST.     

318
00:13:57,537 --> 00:13:59,937
  <i> PAUL SAYS GODDARD TRAINED</i>    
       <i> AS A PHYSICIAN,</i>         

319
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:02,873
     <i> BUT IN 1926, ENTERED</i>      
      <i> THE EMERGING FIELD</i>       

320
00:14:02,942 --> 00:14:04,341
    <i> OF BALLISTIC SCIENCE.</i>      

321
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:05,910
      <i> HIS FORENSIC WORK,</i>       

322
00:14:05,978 --> 00:14:08,546
     <i> WHICH HELPED CONVICT</i>      
    <i> ANARCHIST NICOLA SACCO</i>     

323
00:14:08,614 --> 00:14:11,615
   <i> IN THE CELEBRATED SACCO</i>     
  <i> AND VANZETTI MURDER CASE,</i>    

324
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:14,051
     <i> CAUGHT THE ATTENTION</i>      
   <i> OF THE CHICAGO CORONER.</i>     

325
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:17,154
IT WAS THE ENORMITY OF          
THE ST. VALENTINE'S DAY MASSACRE

326
00:14:17,223 --> 00:14:20,724
THAT BROUGHT THE NEED           
FOR SCIENTIFIC CRIME DETECTION  

327
00:14:20,793 --> 00:14:22,593
TO THE PUBLIC ATTENTION         

328
00:14:22,662 --> 00:14:24,995
AND TO THE ATTENTION            
OF AUTHORITIES OF CHICAGO.      

329
00:14:25,064 --> 00:14:27,731
      <i> GODDARD TEST-FIRED</i>       
  <i> THE BURKE RAID TOMMY GUNS</i>    

330
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,600
   <i> AND COMPARED THE SHELLS</i>     
           <i> TO THOSE</i>            

331
00:14:29,669 --> 00:14:31,268
 <i> FROM THE SCENE OF THE CRIME.</i>  

332
00:14:31,337 --> 00:14:33,370
       <i> HE EXPLAINED TO</i>         
  <i> THE CHICAGO INVESTIGATORS</i>    

333
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:36,507
     <i> HOW SPENT SHELLS HAD</i>      
 <i> THEIR OWN IDENTIFYING MARKS.</i>  

334
00:14:36,576 --> 00:14:39,143
HE WOULD PUT THE CARTRIDGE CASES
UNDER THE COMPARISON MICROSCOPE,

335
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:40,844
ONE ON EITHER SIDE.             

336
00:14:40,913 --> 00:14:43,347
THEN HE COMPARED THEM           
THROUGH THE EYEPIECE,           

337
00:14:43,416 --> 00:14:44,715
WHICH IS HERE.                  

338
00:14:44,784 --> 00:14:47,084
            SO, PAUL, TELL ME   
            WHAT I'M LOOKING AT.

339
00:14:47,153 --> 00:14:49,687
       <i> USING A REPLICA</i>         
   <i> OF GODDARD'S MICROSCOPE,</i>    

340
00:14:49,755 --> 00:14:52,456
   <i> PAUL TELLS ME TO COMPARE</i>    
<i> THE IMPRESSIONS ON TWO SHELLS</i>  

341
00:14:52,525 --> 00:14:54,425
        <i> FROM GODDARD'S</i>         
     <i> PERSONAL COLLECTION.</i>      

342
00:14:54,493 --> 00:14:56,527
   SO THE FIRING PIN IMPRESSIONS
   ARE THE SAME.                

343
00:14:56,596 --> 00:14:59,263
         <i> BY MATCHING</i>           
   <i> FIRING PIN IMPRESSIONS,</i>     

344
00:14:59,332 --> 00:15:01,632
   <i> GODDARD DETERMINED THAT</i>     
   <i> FRED BURKE'S TOMMY GUNS</i>     

345
00:15:01,701 --> 00:15:03,334
  <i> WERE USED IN THE MASSACRE.</i>   

346
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:05,135
              SO THESE CAME     
              FROM THE SAME GUN.

347
00:15:05,204 --> 00:15:07,238
      WELL, I HAVE THESE SHELLS,

348
00:15:07,306 --> 00:15:10,040
         AND I SHOT THESE SHELLS
         FROM MIKE'S GUN.       

349
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:12,376
     <i> PAUL OFFERS TO TAKE</i>       
        <i> A CLOSER LOOK.</i>         

350
00:15:12,445 --> 00:15:14,912
<i> ALTHOUGH THE CARTRIDGE SHELLS</i>  
     <i> FROM THE CRIME SCENE</i>      

351
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:17,948
    <i> ARE LONG GONE, HE SAYS</i>     
   <i> GODDARD DID EXAMINE THEM</i>    

352
00:15:18,017 --> 00:15:21,018
    <i> AND TESTIFIED IN FRONT</i>     
 <i> OF THE CORONER'S GRAND JURY.</i>  

353
00:15:21,087 --> 00:15:23,887
THE CHARACTERISTICS             
THAT GODDARD EMPHASIZED         

354
00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:25,589
IN HIS TESTIMONY, THOUGH,       

355
00:15:25,658 --> 00:15:27,691
WERE THE EXTRACTOR              
AND EJECTOR MARKS.              

356
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,194
EXTRACTOR MARKS ARE             
THE MARKINGS THAT OCCUR         

357
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,863
WHEN A SHELL IS                 
IN THE CHAMBER OF A GUN         

358
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,932
AND IS EXTRACTED                
FROM THE CHAMBER,               

359
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:36,867
AND AN EJECTOR MARKING OCCURS   

360
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:39,003
WHEN THE SHELL IS KICKED OUT    
OF THE GUN.                     

361
00:15:39,071 --> 00:15:41,772
     <i> WE TAKE A CLOSE LOOK</i>      
        <i> AT OUR SHELLS.</i>         

362
00:15:41,841 --> 00:15:43,540
 OH, THOSE TWO LITTLE SCRATCHES?

363
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,275
THAT IS CORRECT.                
                     I SEE THEM.

364
00:15:45,344 --> 00:15:46,810
   <i> WHAT PAUL TELLS ME NEXT</i>     

365
00:15:46,879 --> 00:15:49,079
   <i> IS CERTAINLY GOING TO BE</i>    
     <i> OF INTEREST TO MIKE.</i>      

366
00:15:49,148 --> 00:15:51,415
             INVESTIGATORS FOUND
             BULLETS AND SHELLS 

367
00:15:51,484 --> 00:15:52,883
      AT THE SCENE OF THE CRIME,

368
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,552
   AND TWO OF THOSE SHELLS      
   WERE FROM A 12-GAUGE SHOTGUN,

369
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,354
                THE SAME GAUGE  
                AS YOUR SHOTGUN.

370
00:15:57,423 --> 00:15:58,956
THAT GETS US VERY CLOSE.        

371
00:15:59,025 --> 00:16:02,059
 <i> I TELL MIKE THAT THE STRANGE</i>  
 <i> CARVED NOTCHES ON HIS WEAPON</i>  

372
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:04,228
       <i> COULD HAVE BEEN</i>         
    <i> A GANGSTER SIGNATURE,</i>      

373
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:06,897
    <i> INDICATING THE WEAPON</i>      
  <i> HAD BEEN USED IN A MURDER.</i>   

374
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,233
       <i> SIMILAR MARKINGS</i>        
      <i> HAD ALSO BEEN SEEN</i>       

375
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:12,269
<i> ON THE THOMPSON SUBMACHINE GUNS</i>
    <i> USED IN THE MASSACRE.</i>      

376
00:16:12,338 --> 00:16:15,105
  <i> ALTHOUGH MISSING EVIDENCE</i>    
   <i> MADE A DIRECT COMPARISON</i>    

377
00:16:15,174 --> 00:16:17,674
       <i> WITH HIS SHELLS</i>         
      <i> IMPOSSIBLE TODAY,</i>        

378
00:16:17,743 --> 00:16:19,610
 <i> AT THE TIME OF THE MASSACRE,</i>  

379
00:16:19,678 --> 00:16:21,612
    <i> THE EXPERT BROUGHT IN</i>      
      <i> BY THE AUTHORITIES</i>       

380
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:24,581
   <i> HAD CONDUCTED A THOROUGH</i>    
   <i> FORENSIC INVESTIGATION.</i>     

381
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:27,451
     GODDARD DID CLOSELY EXAMINE
     THE SHELLS THAT WERE FOUND 

382
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,253
      AT THE SCENE OF THE CRIME,

383
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:31,855
          AND HE MADE A PRETTY  
          INTERESTING DISCOVERY.

384
00:16:31,924 --> 00:16:33,791
THESE ARE THE TYPES             
OF MARKINGS                     

385
00:16:33,859 --> 00:16:37,294
THAT GODDARD FOUND ON THE SHELLS
FROM THE SCENE OF THE CRIME.    

386
00:16:37,363 --> 00:16:39,897
    <i> GODDARD HAD DETERMINED</i>     
    <i> THAT THE SHOTGUN USED</i>      

387
00:16:39,965 --> 00:16:43,867
  <i> IN THE MURDER OF SEVEN MEN</i>   
<i> ON ST. VALENTINE'S DAY, 1929,</i>  

388
00:16:43,936 --> 00:16:47,638
 <i> WAS A PUMP-ACTION GUN, TOO,</i>   
     <i> THE SAME AS MIKE'S.</i>       

389
00:16:47,706 --> 00:16:48,972
             SO IN YOUR OPINION,

390
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:50,474
   COULD THIS GUN HAVE BEEN USED
   IN THE MASSACRE?             

391
00:16:50,543 --> 00:16:51,542
    YES.                        

392
00:16:51,610 --> 00:16:53,010
IT IS THE RIGHT VINTAGE.        

393
00:16:53,078 --> 00:16:55,212
IT HAS BOTH THE EXTRACTOR       
AND EJECTOR MARKINGS            

394
00:16:55,281 --> 00:16:57,281
WHICH GODDARD IDENTIFIED.       

395
00:16:57,349 --> 00:17:00,117
       WE CAN PROVE THAT THE GUN
       THAT WAS SHOT THAT DAY   

396
00:17:00,186 --> 00:17:02,219
              WAS A 12-GAUGE    
              REPEATING SHOTGUN.

397
00:17:02,288 --> 00:17:04,521
          YOUR GUN IS A 12-GAUGE
          REPEATING SHOTGUN.    

398
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:06,490
RIGHT, RIGHT.                   
THAT'S GREAT.                   

399
00:17:06,559 --> 00:17:08,826
    <i> I TELL MIKE THERE ARE</i>      
 <i> NO SURVIVING POLICE RECORDS</i>   

400
00:17:08,894 --> 00:17:11,395
     <i> OF ANY OTHER SHOTGUN</i>      
  <i> BEING RECOVERED BY POLICE</i>    

401
00:17:11,464 --> 00:17:12,930
  <i> AND TIED TO THE KILLINGS.</i>    

402
00:17:12,998 --> 00:17:16,099
WHILE WE CAN'T CONCLUSIVELY LINK
YOUR GUN TO THE MASSACRE,       

403
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:17,801
       NO EVIDENCE RULES IT OUT.

404
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,069
VERY INTERESTING.               

405
00:17:19,138 --> 00:17:21,305
       SO IF THE ORIGINAL SHELLS
       SURFACE,                 

406
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:23,540
        THEN WE WOULD BE ABLE   
        TO FINISH GODDARD'S WORK

407
00:17:23,609 --> 00:17:25,509
       AND DETERMINE IF YOUR GUN
       FIRED THEM.              

408
00:17:25,578 --> 00:17:27,010
         HOW DO YOU THINK       
         YOUR FATHER WOULD FEEL,

409
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:28,445
        THE FACT THAT WE'VE COME
        THIS FAR?               

410
00:17:28,514 --> 00:17:30,480
HE WOULD BE ECSTATIC.           

411
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:32,382
HE WOULD SAY,                   
"I TOLD YOU SO."                

412
00:17:32,451 --> 00:17:34,651
THANK YOU, THANK YOU VERY MUCH. 

413
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,454
<i> FRED BURKE WAS NEVER CONVICTED</i> 
      <i> FOR THE MASSACRE.</i>        

414
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:38,956
   <i> INSTEAD, HE WAS PUT AWAY</i>    

415
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:41,692
  <i> FOR KILLING POLICE OFFICER</i>   
       <i> CHARLES SKELLY.</i>         

416
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:45,963
<i> CAPONE WAS EVENTUALLY BROUGHT</i>  
<i> DOWN ON CHARGES OF TAX EVASION.</i>

417
00:17:46,031 --> 00:17:48,031
      <i> BUT GODDARD'S WORK</i>       
     <i> BROUGHT CREDIBILITY</i>       

418
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,000
      <i> TO THE YOUNG FIELD</i>       
        <i> OF BALLISTICS.</i>         

419
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:51,835
    <i> HE WAS GIVEN RESOURCES</i>     
           <i> TO OPEN</i>             

420
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:54,371
  <i> ONE OF THE NATION'S FIRST</i>    
    <i> INDEPENDENT CRIME LABS</i>     

421
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:56,473
   <i> AND CONTINUED TO PIONEER</i>    
          <i> TECHNIQUES</i>           

422
00:17:56,542 --> 00:17:59,076
  <i> THAT ARE STILL USED TODAY.</i>   

423
00:17:59,144 --> 00:18:01,411
   FOR MORE OF MY INTERVIEW     
        WITH ART BELIK,         

424
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:04,848
   VISIT<i> HISTORY DETECTIVES</i>     
    ON THE WEB AT pbs.org.      

425
00:18:07,386 --> 00:18:09,853
       THE GUN THAT MADE        
         THE '20s ROAR          

426
00:18:09,922 --> 00:18:13,423
  WAS INSPIRED BY WORLD WAR I   
        TRENCH WARFARE.         

427
00:18:13,492 --> 00:18:15,926
  THE THOMPSON SUBMACHINE GUN   
         WAS DESIGNED           

428
00:18:15,995 --> 00:18:19,129
      BY RETIRED GENERAL        
        JOHN THOMPSON.          

429
00:18:19,198 --> 00:18:21,932
      EARLY MACHINE GUNS        
     WERE EXTREMELY HEAVY       

430
00:18:22,001 --> 00:18:24,368
     AND TOOK SEVERAL MEN       
          TO OPERATE.           

431
00:18:24,436 --> 00:18:27,738
    THOMPSON'S SOLUTION WAS     
     A RAPID-FIRING WEAPON      

432
00:18:27,806 --> 00:18:30,240
          OPERATED BY           
       A SINGLE SOLDIER.        

433
00:18:30,309 --> 00:18:32,509
      THE "TRENCH BROOM"        
         WAS DESIGNED           

434
00:18:32,578 --> 00:18:35,379
      TO SWEEP THE ENEMY        
       OUT OF FOXHOLES.         

435
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:38,382
   BUT THE GUN WASN'T READY     
  UNTIL AFTER THE WAR ENDED,    

436
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:42,185
SO THE GENERAL TRIED SELLING IT 
    TO THE AMERICAN PUBLIC.     

437
00:18:42,254 --> 00:18:44,454
   ONE NOTORIOUS AD FEATURED    

438
00:18:44,523 --> 00:18:47,324
 A COWBOY DEFENDING HIS RANCH   
         FROM BANDITS.          

439
00:18:47,393 --> 00:18:50,827
 DEEMED SIMPLE, SAFE, STURDY,   
      AND SURE IN ACTION,       

440
00:18:50,896 --> 00:18:55,465
 AN ORIGINAL TOMMY COULD FIRE   
   1,500 ROUNDS PER MINUTE.     

441
00:18:55,534 --> 00:18:58,802
 GANGSTERS SAW THE POTENTIAL.   

442
00:18:58,871 --> 00:19:02,072
  THE GUN WAS SUCH A FAVORITE   
      OF THE CHICAGO MOB        

443
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:05,308
    THAT IT WAS ALSO KNOWN      
  AS THE CHICAGO TYPEWRITER,    

444
00:19:05,377 --> 00:19:06,877
      THE CHICAGO PIANO,        

445
00:19:06,945 --> 00:19:09,446
AND THE CHICAGO ORGAN GRINDER.  

446
00:19:09,515 --> 00:19:13,617
FOR CONCEALMENT, THE COMPACT GUN
     COULD BE TOTED AROUND      

447
00:19:13,686 --> 00:19:16,753
         IN A REFITTED          
   MUSICAL INSTRUMENT CASE.     

448
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,623
   THE THOMPSON DID MAKE IT     
      TO THE BATTLEFIELD        

449
00:19:19,692 --> 00:19:21,324
       IN WORLD WAR II.         

450
00:19:21,393 --> 00:19:23,260
     HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS      
         WERE ORDERED           

451
00:19:23,328 --> 00:19:26,663
      AT A COST OF NEARLY       
      $130 MILLION TOTAL.       

452
00:19:26,732 --> 00:19:30,167
    BY THE END OF THE WAR,      
LIGHTER AND CHEAPER COMPETITORS 

453
00:19:30,235 --> 00:19:32,769
   ENDED THE TOMMY'S REIGN.     

454
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:39,242
            Tukufu:             
 <i> OUR NEXT STORY INVESTIGATES</i>   
     <i> A DEATH THREAT SENT</i>       

455
00:19:39,311 --> 00:19:42,479
<i> TO ONE OF THE FIRST PRESIDENTS</i> 
    <i> OF THE UNITED STATES.</i>      

456
00:19:43,749 --> 00:19:46,850
      <i> ON APRIL 14, 1865,</i>       

457
00:19:46,919 --> 00:19:48,885
        <i> A MAN STANDING</i>         
        <i> IN THE SHADOWS</i>         

458
00:19:48,954 --> 00:19:51,388
<i> OF PRESIDENT ABRAHAM LINCOLN'S</i> 
         <i> THEATER BOX</i>           

459
00:19:51,457 --> 00:19:54,024
    <i> FIRED ONE FINAL SHOT.</i>      

460
00:19:54,093 --> 00:19:57,394
<i> IT WAS THE FIRST ASSASSINATION</i> 
  <i> OF AN AMERICAN PRESIDENT,</i>    

461
00:19:57,463 --> 00:20:00,664
<i> AND JOHN WILKES BOOTH'S MOTIVES</i>
     <i> HAVE BEEN QUESTIONED</i>      

462
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:03,467
 <i> AND STUDIED FOR GENERATIONS.</i>  

463
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:06,703
<i> NOW, ALMOST 150 YEARS LATER, </i>  

464
00:20:06,772 --> 00:20:09,506
        <i> MARSHA MULLIN</i>          
   <i> OF NASHVILLE, TENNESSEE,</i>    

465
00:20:09,575 --> 00:20:11,274
   <i> HAS LEARNED OF A LETTER</i>     

466
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:14,644
      <i> SUPPOSEDLY WRITTEN</i>       
<i> BY JOHN WILKES BOOTH'S FATHER</i>  

467
00:20:14,713 --> 00:20:16,713
<i> TO ANOTHER AMERICAN PRESIDENT.</i> 

468
00:20:16,782 --> 00:20:19,616
 TODAY SOMEBODY WOULD BE TAKEN  
  OFF TO JAIL IN FIVE MINUTES   

469
00:20:19,685 --> 00:20:21,384
     FOR WRITING A LETTER       
          LIKE THAT.            

470
00:20:21,453 --> 00:20:23,820
    <i> MARSHA HAS INVITED ME</i>      
      <i> TO THE HERMITAGE,</i>        

471
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:27,224
  <i> PRESIDENT ANDREW JACKSON'S</i>   
  <i> FAMILY HOME IN NASHVILLE,</i>    

472
00:20:27,292 --> 00:20:29,226
 <i> WHERE SHE IS CHIEF CURATOR.</i>   

473
00:20:29,294 --> 00:20:31,428
     SO WHAT DO YOU HAVE FOR ME?

474
00:20:31,497 --> 00:20:33,330
WELL, A COUPLE OF YEARS AGO,    

475
00:20:33,398 --> 00:20:35,899
A VISITOR BROUGHT TO            
OUR ATTENTION THIS LETTER,      

476
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:38,602
WHICH WAS A DEATH THREAT        
TO ANDREW JACKSON               

477
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:40,604
WRITTEN IN 1835.                

478
00:20:40,672 --> 00:20:42,873
I REALLY DIDN'T KNOW            
ANYTHING ABOUT IT,              

479
00:20:42,941 --> 00:20:46,376
SO I GOT A COPY OF IT           
FROM THE LIBRARY OF CONGRESS.   

480
00:20:46,445 --> 00:20:48,945
       <i> THE SIGNATURE ON</i>        
    <i> THE DEATH THREAT READS</i>     

481
00:20:49,014 --> 00:20:50,947
     <i> JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH.</i>      

482
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:53,850
JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH             
WAS A VERY FAMOUS ACTOR,        

483
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,752
BUT INTERESTINGLY ENOUGH,       

484
00:20:55,821 --> 00:20:58,321
HE WAS ALSO THE FATHER          
OF JOHN WILKES BOOTH.           

485
00:20:58,390 --> 00:21:00,156
      NOW, THAT'S AN INTERESTING
      CONNECTION.               

486
00:21:00,225 --> 00:21:01,825
IT'S VERY INTERESTING.          

487
00:21:01,894 --> 00:21:05,595
          <i> IT'S DATED</i>           
    <i> THE 4th OF JULY, 1835,</i>     

488
00:21:05,664 --> 00:21:08,398
     <i> FROM BROWER'S HOTEL,</i>      
        <i> PHILADELPHIA.</i>          

489
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:10,533
      "YOU DAMNED OLD SCOUNDREL,

490
00:21:10,602 --> 00:21:14,404
       I WILL CUT YOUR THROAT   
       WHILST YOU ARE SLEEPING."

491
00:21:14,473 --> 00:21:18,642
 <i> HE'S INSISTING THAT JACKSON</i>   
 <i> PARDON TWO MEN ON DEATH ROW.</i>  

492
00:21:18,710 --> 00:21:20,744
            "I'LL HAVE YOU BURNT
            AT THE STAKE        

493
00:21:20,812 --> 00:21:22,545
     "IN THE CITY OF WASHINGTON.

494
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:26,983
           YOUR MASTER,         
           JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH."

495
00:21:27,052 --> 00:21:29,586
      MAN, NOW THIS IS A THREAT.

496
00:21:29,655 --> 00:21:32,188
        SO THE FATHER OF THE GUY
        WHO KILLED LINCOLN      

497
00:21:32,257 --> 00:21:34,557
       THREATENED TO ASSASSINATE
       A PRESIDENT.             

498
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:36,593
WELL, THAT'S THE QUESTION.      

499
00:21:36,662 --> 00:21:39,029
BECAUSE WHEN YOU LOOK           
AT THE BACK OF THE LETTER,      

500
00:21:39,097 --> 00:21:41,364
SOMEONE HAS WRITTEN             
"ANONYMOUS."                    

501
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:43,700
AND SO THAT WAS VERY CURIOUS.   

502
00:21:43,769 --> 00:21:45,969
IS IT BY JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH    
OR NOT?                         

503
00:21:46,038 --> 00:21:48,138
JACKSON SCHOLARS                
SEEM TO BELIEVE                 

504
00:21:48,206 --> 00:21:50,607
THAT IT WAS WRITTEN             
BY SOMEONE ELSE.                

505
00:21:50,676 --> 00:21:53,143
WE'D LIKE TO KNOW               
IF JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH          

506
00:21:53,211 --> 00:21:56,246
REALLY WROTE THIS LETTER,       
AND IF HE DID, WHY?             

507
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:59,749
  WELL, LET ME SEE IF I CAN FIND
  AN ANSWER TO YOUR QUESTION.   

508
00:21:59,818 --> 00:22:01,418
     <i> THE SINS OF A FATHER</i>      

509
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:04,521
 <i> ARE NOT NECESSARILY VISITED</i>   
        <i> UPON THE SON.</i>          

510
00:22:04,589 --> 00:22:08,124
<i> BUT PRESIDENT LINCOLN'S MURDER</i> 
  <i> ALTERED AMERICAN HISTORY.</i>    

511
00:22:08,193 --> 00:22:10,393
<i> IF JOHN WILKES BOOTH'S FATHER</i>  

512
00:22:10,462 --> 00:22:12,962
   <i> ALSO THREATENED THE LIFE</i>    
   <i> OF A SITTING PRESIDENT,</i>     

513
00:22:13,031 --> 00:22:18,401
 <i> THAT'S CERTAINLY INTERESTING</i>  
  <i> AND POSSIBLY SIGNIFICANT.</i>    

514
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:21,738
<i> JACKSON WAS THE 7th PRESIDENT</i>  
     <i> OF THE UNITED STATES</i>      

515
00:22:21,807 --> 00:22:24,974
    <i> AND FIRST TOOK OFFICE</i>      
           <i> IN 1829.</i>            

516
00:22:25,043 --> 00:22:29,946
 <i> JUNIUS BOOTH WAS</i> THE<i> POPULAR</i>  
<i> SHAKESPEAREAN ACTOR OF THE DAY.</i>

517
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:33,483
       <i> THE QUESTION IS,</i>        
 <i> WHY HAVE HISTORIANS DOUBTED</i>   

518
00:22:33,552 --> 00:22:37,187
 <i> THAT JUNIUS BOOTH WROTE THIS</i>  
     <i> IN THE FIRST PLACE?</i>       

519
00:22:37,255 --> 00:22:40,757
       <i> MARSHA'S LEFT ME</i>        
  <i> 20th-CENTURY PUBLICATIONS</i>    

520
00:22:40,826 --> 00:22:42,559
    <i> OF A JACKSON BIOGRAPHY</i>     

521
00:22:42,627 --> 00:22:44,961
       <i> AND A COLLECTION</i>        
    <i> OF HIS CORRESPONDENCE.</i>     

522
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:48,231
 <i> BOTH VOLUMES INCLUDE MENTION</i>  
        <i> OF OUR LETTER.</i>         

523
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:53,036
   JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH HERE     
    IS IN QUOTATION MARKS.      

524
00:22:53,105 --> 00:22:56,873
  BOOTH, IN QUOTATION MARKS,    
      TO ANDREW JACKSON,        

525
00:22:56,942 --> 00:22:59,442
         JULY 4, 1835.          

526
00:22:59,511 --> 00:23:02,846
 <i> THE QUOTATION MARKS INDICATE</i>  
   <i> THE AUTHORS AND EDITORS</i>     

527
00:23:02,914 --> 00:23:06,049
<i> ALSO DOUBTED THAT BOOTH WROTE</i>  
      <i> THE DEATH THREAT.</i>        

528
00:23:06,118 --> 00:23:09,519
      I NEED TO FOUND OUT       
        IF THESE DOUBTS         

529
00:23:09,588 --> 00:23:12,555
         ARE BASED ON           
     SOME ACTUAL EVIDENCE.      

530
00:23:12,624 --> 00:23:15,692
      <i> THE LETTER WRITER,</i>       
       <i> WHOEVER HE WAS,</i>         

531
00:23:15,761 --> 00:23:19,095
   <i> WANTED TWO MEN PARDONED:</i>    
     <i> DE RUIZ AND DE SOTO.</i>      

532
00:23:19,164 --> 00:23:21,664
  <i> I WONDER WHAT OTHER CLUES</i>    
       <i> THERE MIGHT BE.</i>         

533
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:23,766
       IT SAYS DOWN HERE        
       IN A POSTSCRIPT,         

534
00:23:23,835 --> 00:23:26,169
   "YOU KNOW ME, LOOK OUT."     

535
00:23:26,238 --> 00:23:28,972
       DOES IT MEAN THAT        
    HE KNEW HIM PERSONALLY?     

536
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:31,174
         DOES IT MEAN           
     THAT HE KNEW OF HIM?       

537
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:33,810
        "I WROTE TO YOU         
