548
00:24:02,674 --> 00:24:06,376
OUR ASSUMPTION IS THAT THE      
ORIGINAL NOTATION WAS CORRECT,  

549
00:24:06,444 --> 00:24:08,077
THAT IT'S ANONYMOUS.            

550
00:24:08,146 --> 00:24:11,748
      <i> DAN EXPLAINS THAT</i>        
<i> PRESIDENT JACKSON'S STRONG-HAND</i>

551
00:24:11,816 --> 00:24:14,150
 <i> AND OFTEN UNPOPULAR POLICIES</i>  

552
00:24:14,219 --> 00:24:17,987
 <i> HAD MADE HIM A LIGHTNING ROD</i>  
  <i> FOR CRITICISM AND THREATS.</i>   

553
00:24:18,056 --> 00:24:20,557
      <i> SIX MONTHS BEFORE</i>        
   <i> OUR LETTER WAS WRITTEN,</i>     

554
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:23,426
     <i> HE WAS THE VICTIM OF</i>      
<i> THE FIRST ASSASSINATION ATTEMPT</i>

555
00:24:23,495 --> 00:24:25,895
<i> AGAINST AN AMERICAN PRESIDENT.</i> 

556
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:28,898
   <i> A DERANGED HOUSE PAINTER</i>    
    <i> ATTEMPTED TO SHOOT HIM</i>     

557
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:32,635
<i> OUTSIDE THE CAPITOL BUILDING,</i>  
   <i> BUT THE PISTOL MISFIRED.</i>    

558
00:24:32,704 --> 00:24:35,438
SHORTLY AFTER THAT,             
THE<i> WASHINGTON GLOBE</i> PUBLISHED  

559
00:24:35,507 --> 00:24:38,107
SEVERAL COLUMNS                 
OF ASSASSINATION LETTERS        

560
00:24:38,176 --> 00:24:40,243
THAT IT SAID JACKSON            
HAD RECEIVED.                   

561
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:42,078
LET ME PUT THESE UP             
ON OUR COMPUTER SCREEN          

562
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:43,446
SO YOU CAN READ THEM BETTER.    

563
00:24:43,515 --> 00:24:44,847
HERE'S ONE.                     

564
00:24:44,916 --> 00:24:46,749
            "DAMN YOUR OLD SOUL,

565
00:24:46,818 --> 00:24:49,752
    "IF YOU DO NOT DO SOMETHING 
    FOR THE GOOD OF THE COUNTRY,

566
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:51,521
             I WILL MURDER YOU."

567
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:52,755
                      WOW.      

568
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:55,091
       <i> DAN SAYS JACKSON</i>        
    <i> DREW PUBLIC CRITICISM</i>      

569
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:57,026
 <i> BECAUSE HE WANTED TO DO AWAY</i>  

570
00:24:57,095 --> 00:24:59,862
 <i> WITH THE FEDERALLY CHARTERED</i>  
  <i> BANK OF THE UNITED STATES,</i>   

571
00:24:59,931 --> 00:25:03,232
   <i> WHICH HE REGARDED AS AN</i>     
<i> UNCONSTITUTIONAL CONCENTRATION</i> 

572
00:25:03,301 --> 00:25:04,934
     <i> OF FINANCIAL POWER.</i>       

573
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:06,436
HERE'S ANOTHER ONE:             

574
00:25:06,504 --> 00:25:08,972
"REMOVE THEM DEPOSITS BACK AGAIN
AND RECHARTER THE BANK,         

575
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:11,407
"OR YOU WILL CERTAINLY BE SHOT  
IN LESS THAN TWO WEEKS,         

576
00:25:11,476 --> 00:25:13,209
AND THAT BY MYSELF!"            

577
00:25:13,278 --> 00:25:17,046
THE UNITED STATES SENATE        
ACTUALLY CENSURED JACKSON       

578
00:25:17,115 --> 00:25:19,949
FOR REMOVING THE DEPOSITS,      
THE ONLY TIME A PRESIDENT       

579
00:25:20,018 --> 00:25:21,851
HAS EVER BEEN CENSURED          
BY THE SENATE.                  

580
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:25,655
<i> DAN SAYS T RUIZ AND DE SOTO</i>    
   <i> MENTIONED IN OUR LETTER</i>     

581
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:28,358
<i> WERE SPANISH PIRATES OPERATING</i> 
        <i> OUT OF HAVANA.</i>         

582
00:25:28,426 --> 00:25:30,460
       <i> WITH TEN OTHERS,</i>        
       <i> THEY HAD ROBBED</i>         

583
00:25:30,528 --> 00:25:34,630
  <i> AN AMERICAN MERCHANT SHIP</i>    
      <i> IN SEPTEMBER 1832.</i>       

584
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:37,633
     <i> THE PIRATES' CAPTURE</i>      
     <i> AND SUBSEQUENT TRIAL</i>      

585
00:25:37,702 --> 00:25:39,569
   <i> ELECTRIFIED THE NATION.</i>     

586
00:25:39,637 --> 00:25:41,337
THIS WAS A HUGE CASE.           

587
00:25:41,406 --> 00:25:44,574
IT HAD ALL OF THE ASPECTS       
OF A MODERN SHOW TRIAL.         

588
00:25:44,642 --> 00:25:46,876
    <i> ONE OF THE SPANIARDS,</i>      
           <i> DE SOTO,</i>            

589
00:25:46,945 --> 00:25:50,146
   <i> WAS PARDONED MOST LIKELY</i>    
<i> BECAUSE HE PREVIOUSLY HAD SAVED</i>

590
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:52,882
      <i> THE LIVES OF SOME</i>        
      <i> AMERICAN SAILORS.</i>        

591
00:25:52,951 --> 00:25:56,119
     <i> DAN SAYS THE PARDON</i>       
   <i> WAS ALMOST CERTAINLY NOT</i>    

592
00:25:56,187 --> 00:25:58,621
         <i> AS A RESULT</i>           
     <i> OF THE DEATH THREAT.</i>      

593
00:25:58,690 --> 00:26:01,023
              HOW SERIOUSLY WAS 
              THIS THREAT TAKEN?

594
00:26:01,092 --> 00:26:03,926
     <i> DAN DOUBTS THERE WAS</i>      
  <i> ANY OFFICIAL INVESTIGATION</i>   

595
00:26:03,995 --> 00:26:05,328
       <i> INTO THE LETTER.</i>        

596
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:07,397
 <i> THE OFFICE OF THE PRESIDENT</i>   
         <i> DID NOT HAVE</i>          

597
00:26:07,465 --> 00:26:09,632
    <i> THE PROTECTIVE LAYERS</i>      
        <i> IT HAS TODAY.</i>          

598
00:26:09,701 --> 00:26:11,601
THERE WAS NO SECRET SERVICE,    

599
00:26:11,669 --> 00:26:14,003
THERE WAS NO FEDERAL BUREAU     
OF INVESTIGATION,               

600
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:16,272
THERE WERE REALLY               
NO WHITE HOUSE POLICE.          

601
00:26:16,341 --> 00:26:17,974
IN FACT, ASSASSINATING          
THE PRESIDENT                   

602
00:26:18,042 --> 00:26:20,076
OR THREATENING TO DO SO         
WAS NOT A FEDERAL CRIME.        

603
00:26:20,145 --> 00:26:23,813
   HERE HE SAYS, "I WROTE TO YOU
   REPEATED CAUTIONS."          

604
00:26:23,882 --> 00:26:26,215
            DO YOU KNOW OF ANY  
            OTHER COMMUNICATIONS

605
00:26:26,284 --> 00:26:27,984
      BETWEEN BOOTH AND JACKSON?

606
00:26:28,052 --> 00:26:29,786
IF THERE WERE ANY,              
WE WOULD HAVE SEEN THEM.        

607
00:26:29,854 --> 00:26:31,387
WE KNOW OF ONE LETTER           

608
00:26:31,456 --> 00:26:34,290
FROM SOMEONE CALLING HIMSELF    
JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH TO JACKSON, 

609
00:26:34,359 --> 00:26:35,491
AND THIS IS IT.                 

610
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:36,726
                  AND THAT'S IT.

611
00:26:36,795 --> 00:26:39,095
AND NOT ONLY NO LETTERS         
FROM BOOTH OR TO BOOTH,         

612
00:26:39,164 --> 00:26:41,898
BUT NO MENTION OF BOOTH         
IN JACKSON'S CORRESPONDENCE.    

613
00:26:41,966 --> 00:26:44,167
        <i> WHOEVER WANTED</i>         
   <i> THESE PIRATES PARDONED,</i>     

614
00:26:44,235 --> 00:26:46,402
       <i> DAN'S CONVINCED</i>         
       <i> IT WASN'T BOOTH.</i>        

615
00:26:46,471 --> 00:26:48,971
EVERY HISTORIAN                 
PREVIOUS TO US,                 

616
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,606
EVERY JACKSON BIOGRAPHER,       

617
00:26:50,675 --> 00:26:52,275
HAS ASSUMED THAT BOOTH          
DIDN'T WRITE IT.                

618
00:26:52,343 --> 00:26:53,676
SOMEONE IN HIS OFFICE --        

619
00:26:53,745 --> 00:26:55,344
AND HE HAD A NUMBER OF CLERKS   
WORKING FOR HIM --              

620
00:26:55,413 --> 00:26:57,814
PROBABLY WROTE THIS WORD        
"ANONYMOUS."                    

621
00:26:57,882 --> 00:26:59,081
       JACKSON DID NOT WRITE IT.

622
00:26:59,150 --> 00:27:01,284
IT DOESN'T APPEAR TO BE         
JACKSON'S HANDWRITING, NO.      

623
00:27:01,352 --> 00:27:03,252
      HAS THERE BEEN AN ANALYSIS

624
00:27:03,321 --> 00:27:05,121
              OF THE HANDWRITING
              IN THIS LETTER?   

625
00:27:05,190 --> 00:27:07,623
AS FAR AS I KNOW, NO ONE HAS    
EVER TAKEN IT TO THAT STEP      

626
00:27:07,692 --> 00:27:09,859
BECAUSE THEY THOUGHT            
IT WAS UNNECESSARY.             

627
00:27:09,928 --> 00:27:13,196
<i> THAT SEEMS A CURIOUS OMISSION.</i> 

628
00:27:13,264 --> 00:27:16,332
<i> THE FOLGER SHAKESPEARE LIBRARY</i> 
     <i> IN WASHINGTON, D.C.,</i>      

629
00:27:16,401 --> 00:27:19,969
   <i> HAS SEVERAL JUNIUS BOOTH</i>    
 <i> LETTERS IN THEIR COLLECTION.</i>  

630
00:27:20,038 --> 00:27:22,838
   <i> HEATHER WOLFE IS CURATOR</i>    
       <i> OF MANUSCRIPTS.</i>         

631
00:27:22,907 --> 00:27:25,575
<i> SHE'S MADE SPECIAL ARRANGEMENTS</i>
 <i> WITH THE LIBRARY OF CONGRESS</i>  

632
00:27:25,643 --> 00:27:27,944
<i> TO OBTAIN THE ORIGINAL THREAT</i>  
         <i> TO JACKSON.</i>           

633
00:27:28,012 --> 00:27:29,612
HEATHER, NICE TO MEET YOU.      

634
00:27:29,681 --> 00:27:32,481
SO THIS IS THE ORIGINAL LETTER. 

635
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:36,285
I PICKED TWO OF OUR             
JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH LETTERS     

636
00:27:36,354 --> 00:27:37,987
FOR A HANDWRITING ANALYSIS.     

637
00:27:38,056 --> 00:27:39,622
I PICKED THESE TWO LETTERS      

638
00:27:39,691 --> 00:27:42,491
BECAUSE THEY WERE CLOSEST       
IN DATE AND FORMAT              

639
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:45,394
TO THE 1835 LETTER              
TO GENERAL JACKSON.             

640
00:27:45,463 --> 00:27:47,330
     <i> IT'S THE FIRST TIME</i>       
       <i> HEATHER HAS SEEN</i>        

641
00:27:47,398 --> 00:27:49,165
     <i> THE ORIGINAL LETTER</i>       
         <i> TO JACKSON,</i>           

642
00:27:49,234 --> 00:27:51,500
    <i> AND A COUPLE OF ITEMS</i>      
      <i> STRIKE HER AS ODD.</i>       

643
00:27:51,569 --> 00:27:54,470
HE SIGNS THE LETTER TO JACKSON  
WITH HIS FULL NAME,             

644
00:27:54,539 --> 00:27:56,205
JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH.            

645
00:27:56,274 --> 00:27:59,442
ALL OF THE LETTERS AT THE FOLGER
ARE SIGNED J.B. BOOTH,          

646
00:27:59,510 --> 00:28:01,877
AND THAT WAS HIS TYPICAL        
SIGNATURE.                      

647
00:28:01,946 --> 00:28:03,713
    <i> THE REST OF THE LETTER</i>     
         <i> LOOKS AS IF</i>           

648
00:28:03,781 --> 00:28:05,881
      <i> IT COULD'VE FLOWED</i>       
      <i> FROM THE SAME PEN.</i>       

649
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:09,552
AND YOU SEE HERE, "I WROTE      
TO YOU REPEATED CAUTIONS,"      

650
00:28:09,621 --> 00:28:11,387
AND SEE THE BOTTOM OF THAT C,   

651
00:28:11,456 --> 00:28:13,422
HOW IT LOOPS AROUND             
DRAMATICALLY?                   

652
00:28:13,491 --> 00:28:16,025
WELL, IN THIS LETTER HERE,      
WE SEE THE WORD "CAMP"          

653
00:28:16,094 --> 00:28:20,296
WITH THAT SAME VERY DISTINCTIVE 
MAJUSCULE C,                    

654
00:28:20,365 --> 00:28:24,333
WHICH IS VERY UNIQUE            
TO JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH.         

655
00:28:24,402 --> 00:28:27,036
ONE OF THE MOST DISTINCTIVE     
ATTRIBUTES HE HAS               

656
00:28:27,105 --> 00:28:30,072
IS THE CROSSBAR                 
ON THE MINISCULE T's.           

657
00:28:30,141 --> 00:28:33,376
SO IF YOU LOOK AT THE WORD "THE"
IN THIS LETTER,                 

658
00:28:33,444 --> 00:28:36,946
THE CROSSBAR GOES FULLY ACROSS  
NOT JUST THE T                  

659
00:28:37,015 --> 00:28:38,881
BUT ALSO THE H AND THE E.       

660
00:28:38,950 --> 00:28:41,250
  <i> IF BOOTH DIDN'T WRITE THIS</i>   
           <i> HIMSELF,</i>            

661
00:28:41,319 --> 00:28:46,355
   <i> SHE SAYS THE FORGER WAS</i>     
   <i> AT THE TOP OF HIS CLASS.</i>    

662
00:28:46,424 --> 00:28:48,691
        <i> HEATHER'S MADE</i>         
      <i> ANOTHER DISCOVERY.</i>       

663
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:51,193
THIS LETTER FROM 1834           

664
00:28:51,262 --> 00:28:54,897
MENTIONS THAT HE NEEDED         
TO ESCAPE THE FARM              

665
00:28:54,966 --> 00:28:57,299
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS            
AND GO TO PHILADELPHIA,         

666
00:28:57,368 --> 00:29:00,069
AND IT SAYS, "THEREFORE         
I STROLLED TO PHILADELPHIA.     

667
00:29:00,138 --> 00:29:03,806
BROWER'S HOTEL IS NOW           
ABOUT THE BEST IN THAT CITY."   

668
00:29:03,875 --> 00:29:05,841
             SO HE HAS A HISTORY
             OF FREQUENTING     

669
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:08,544
              THE BROWER'S HOTEL
              IN PHILADELPHIA.  

670
00:29:08,613 --> 00:29:09,979
           SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

671
00:29:10,048 --> 00:29:12,815
         DID JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH
         WRITE THIS LETTER?     

672
00:29:12,884 --> 00:29:15,384
BASED ON HANDWRITING ANALYSIS   
ALONE,                          

673
00:29:15,453 --> 00:29:18,587
YES, IT IS A JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH
LETTER.                         

674
00:29:18,656 --> 00:29:20,222
BUT I'M NOT A BOOTH EXPERT,     

675
00:29:20,291 --> 00:29:23,192
SO I THINK THAT'S A QUESTION    
FOR BOOTH SCHOLARS.             

676
00:29:23,261 --> 00:29:25,995
WE'D NEED TO FIND OUT MORE      
ABOUT THE CONTEXT OF THE LETTER.

677
00:29:26,063 --> 00:29:28,531
       <i> WHY DID A FAMOUS</i>        
     <i> SHAKESPEAREAN ACTOR</i>       

678
00:29:28,599 --> 00:29:31,634
  <i> CARE ENOUGH ABOUT THE FATE</i>   
    <i> OF TWO SPANISH PIRATES</i>     

679
00:29:31,702 --> 00:29:33,269
        <i> TO HAVE PENNED</i>         
        <i> A DEATH THREAT</i>         

680
00:29:33,337 --> 00:29:36,038
       <i> TO THE PRESIDENT</i>        
    <i> OF THE UNITED STATES?</i>      

681
00:29:36,107 --> 00:29:38,374
    <i> GENE SMITH HAS AGREED</i>      
          <i> TO MEET ME</i>           

682
00:29:38,443 --> 00:29:41,377
   <i> AT THE FOLGER LIBRARY'S</i>     
     <i> ELIZABETHAN THEATER.</i>      

683
00:29:41,446 --> 00:29:44,113
  <i> HE'S THE AUTHOR OF A BOOK</i>    
<i> ON THE BOOTH FAMILY'S INFLUENCE</i>

684
00:29:44,182 --> 00:29:45,815
     <i> ON AMERICAN THEATER.</i>      

685
00:29:45,883 --> 00:29:47,883
            IN ADDITION TO BEING
            A GREAT ACTOR,      

686
00:29:47,952 --> 00:29:52,721
    JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH WAS     
    A GREAT MADMAN ALL HIS LIFE.

687
00:29:52,790 --> 00:29:54,824
             THERE'S NO QUESTION
             HE WAS INSANE.     

688
00:29:54,892 --> 00:29:58,327
   <i> GENE SAYS THAT THE WILD</i>     
 <i> AND ERRATIC BEHAVIOR ONSTAGE</i>  

689
00:29:58,396 --> 00:30:01,697
    <i> LED BOOTH TO BE DUBBED</i>     
     <i> "THE MAD TRAGEDIAN."</i>      

690
00:30:01,766 --> 00:30:05,167
   HIS BOUTS OF LUNACY          
   COULD INTERRUPT A PRODUCTION.

691
00:30:05,236 --> 00:30:06,869
               HE WOULD RUN AWAY
               FROM THE THEATER 

692
00:30:06,938 --> 00:30:10,339
      AND BE FOUND WALKING NAKED
      DOWN THE STREET.          

693
00:30:10,408 --> 00:30:14,376
  <i> BOOTH'S EXCESSIVE DRINKING</i>   
   <i> EXACERBATED HIS MADNESS.</i>    

694
00:30:14,445 --> 00:30:17,012
               THEATER MANAGERS 
               WOULD LOCK HIM UP

695
00:30:17,081 --> 00:30:19,915
             TO KEEP HIM        
             FROM GETTING DRUNK.

696
00:30:19,984 --> 00:30:22,351
     FREQUENTLY, HE WOULD ESCAPE
     AND SIMPLY VANISH          

697
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:23,919
         FOR THREE OR FOUR DAYS.

698
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:26,522
DID HIS FITS OF MADNESS         
LEAD HIM TO ACTS OF VIOLENCE?   

699
00:30:26,591 --> 00:30:29,658
              YES, BUT ONLY     
              VERY OCCASIONALLY.

700
00:30:29,727 --> 00:30:33,295
     HE WAS CAPABLE IN          
     THE MIDDLE OF A PERFORMANCE

701
00:30:33,364 --> 00:30:40,236
 OF BECOMING SO INVOLVED        
 IN KILLING DESDEMONA AS OTHELLO

702
00:30:40,304 --> 00:30:41,937
       THAT WHEN THE MOMENT CAME

703
00:30:42,006 --> 00:30:45,341
       TO PRESS THE PILLOW      
       AGAINST DESDEMONA'S FACE,

704
00:30:45,409 --> 00:30:48,744
    PEOPLE WERE AFRAID HE WOULD 
    ACTUALLY MURDER THE ACTRESS.

705
00:30:48,813 --> 00:30:51,280
WELL, THIS LETTER               
IS A THREAT                     

706
00:30:51,349 --> 00:30:54,149
TO ASSASSINATE                  
PRESIDENT ANDREW JACKSON.       

707
00:30:54,218 --> 00:30:57,987
COULD THAT VIOLENT BEHAVIOR     
HAVE EXTENDED TO MURDER?        

708
00:30:58,055 --> 00:31:00,089
                 IT IS POSSIBLE.

709
00:31:00,157 --> 00:31:03,058
         HOWEVER, IT'S IMPORTANT
         TO KNOW                

710
00:31:03,127 --> 00:31:06,428
        JUNIUS BRUTUS BOOTH     
        HAD A REVERENCE FOR LIFE

711
00:31:06,497 --> 00:31:09,365
         THAT WAS EXTRAORDINARY.

712
00:31:09,433 --> 00:31:12,568
       GENERALLY, HE HURT NOBODY
       BUT HIMSELF:             

713
00:31:12,637 --> 00:31:15,204
         HIS KIDS WERE FORBIDDEN
         TO SWAT A FLY,         

714
00:31:15,273 --> 00:31:17,640
           HE WOULD NOT CUT DOWN
           A TREE.              

715
00:31:17,708 --> 00:31:20,376
      <i> HIS DEATH THREAT,</i>        
     <i> IF BOOTH PENNED IT,</i>       

716
00:31:20,444 --> 00:31:23,279
     <i> MAY HAVE BEEN A BOUT</i>      
    <i> OF ALCOHOLIC MADNESS,</i>      

717
00:31:23,347 --> 00:31:26,882
    <i> HIS REVERENCE FOR LIFE</i>     
   <i> BIZARRELY PROVOKING HIM</i>     

718
00:31:26,951 --> 00:31:28,951
     <i> TO THREATEN MURDER.</i>       

719
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:32,688
    MY GUESS WOULD BE           
    THAT MR. BOOTH PROBABLY READ

720
00:31:32,757 --> 00:31:36,859
  THAT JACKSON WAS CONSIDERING  
  THE EXECUTION OF THESE TWO MEN

721
00:31:36,927 --> 00:31:40,396
    AND, IN ONE OF HIS FRENZIES,
