906
00:39:41,645 --> 00:39:45,480
<i> WHICH IS A LITTLE ODD IF THIS</i>  
<i> HAD BEEN MANUFACTURED FOR SALE.</i>

907
00:39:45,549 --> 00:39:49,250
<i> I'M SKEPTICAL THIS IS AN ALARM,</i>
      <i> AS HENRY BELIEVES.</i>       

908
00:39:49,319 --> 00:39:53,555
   <i> IT LOOKS MORE LIKE SOME</i>     
<i> KIND OF CIVIL-WAR-ERA WEAPON.</i>  

909
00:39:53,623 --> 00:39:55,456
        THIS IS A BOMB.         

910
00:39:55,525 --> 00:39:58,393
I MEAN, THIS THING WOULD'VE HELD
      MAYBE HALF A POUND,       

911
00:39:58,461 --> 00:40:01,729
   THREE-QUARTERS OF A POUND    
   OF BLACK POWDER IN HERE.     

912
00:40:01,798 --> 00:40:04,799
 <i> IT WEIGHS ABOUT EIGHT POUNDS</i>  
 <i> AND IT'S MADE OF CAST IRON,</i>   

913
00:40:04,868 --> 00:40:07,535
  <i> WHICH WOULD'VE TURNED INTO</i>   
  <i> SHARDS OF DEADLY SHRAPNEL</i>    

914
00:40:07,604 --> 00:40:09,871
        <i> IF THIS THING</i>          
      <i> HAD EVER EXPLODED.</i>       

915
00:40:09,940 --> 00:40:14,275
THIS IS A SPRING-LOADED HAMMER  
    THAT WOULD'VE BEEN SET      

916
00:40:14,344 --> 00:40:19,314
   BY MOVING THIS METAL BAR     
     ON THE COLLAR AROUND.      

917
00:40:19,382 --> 00:40:22,183
  <i> IF SOMEBODY STEPPED ON IT,</i>   
    <i> THIS FIRING MECHANISM</i>      

918
00:40:22,252 --> 00:40:24,852
  <i> WOULD'VE ALMOST CERTAINLY</i>    
     <i> HAVE BEEN ACTIVATED.</i>      

919
00:40:24,921 --> 00:40:27,956
  SO WHEN THIS LITTLE COLLAR    
           IS MOVED             

920
00:40:28,024 --> 00:40:30,525
  EVEN A FRACTION OF AN INCH,   

921
00:40:30,594 --> 00:40:35,096
  THE HAMMER DROPS, AND THEN    
   IT HITS AN EXPLOSIVE CAP,    

922
00:40:35,165 --> 00:40:37,665
    ALMOST LIKE A CAP GUN.      

923
00:40:37,734 --> 00:40:41,069
AND IF YOU LOOK, YOU'LL SEE THAT
THERE'S A HOLE ON THAT NIPPLE,  

924
00:40:41,137 --> 00:40:44,305
    SO A SPARK WOULD TRAVEL     
      INTO THAT INTERIOR,       

925
00:40:44,374 --> 00:40:49,844
     IGNITE THE GUNPOWDER,      
           AND BAM!             

926
00:40:53,149 --> 00:40:55,617
        <i> I'VE COME OUT</i>          
 <i> TO THE CORDOVA DRAGWAY PARK,</i>  

927
00:40:55,685 --> 00:40:57,919
     <i> ABOUT TWO HOURS WEST</i>      
         <i> OF CHICAGO,</i>           

928
00:40:57,988 --> 00:41:01,422
<i> TO SEE JUST HOW DANGEROUS OUR</i>  
<i> EXPLOSIVE DEVICE WOULD'VE BEEN.</i>

929
00:41:01,491 --> 00:41:03,958
        <i> LARRY LEFFERTS</i>         
 <i> OF CENTRAL STATES FIREWORKS</i>   

930
00:41:04,027 --> 00:41:06,027
     <i> CONFIRMED THE AMOUNT</i>      
       <i> OF BLACK POWDER</i>         

931
00:41:06,096 --> 00:41:07,595
 <i> OUR DEVICE WOULD'VE CARRIED.</i>  

932
00:41:07,664 --> 00:41:09,697
WHAT WE DID WAS WE TOOK         
THREE-QUARTERS OF A POUND       

933
00:41:09,766 --> 00:41:11,666
OF BLACK POWDER                 
AND WE BURIED THEM              

934
00:41:11,735 --> 00:41:13,468
AND PUT A LITTLE BIT            
OF DIRT ON TOP                  

935
00:41:13,536 --> 00:41:15,336
TO SIMULATE WHAT                
IT MAY LOOK LIKE.               

936
00:41:15,405 --> 00:41:16,604
FIRE IN THE HOLE!               

937
00:41:18,141 --> 00:41:19,707
FIRE IN THE HOLE!               

938
00:41:19,776 --> 00:41:22,377
             Wes:               
   WHOA, THAT THING COULD DO    
     SOME SERIOUS DAMAGE!       

939
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:27,782
<i> ABOUT AN HOUR FROM THE DRAGWAY</i> 
 <i> IS T ROCK ISLAND ARSENAL.</i>     

940
00:41:27,851 --> 00:41:31,185
     <i> ESTABLISHED IN 1862,</i>      
  <i> IT'S THE NATION'S LARGEST</i>    

941
00:41:31,254 --> 00:41:33,821
       <i> GOVERNMENT-OWNED</i>        
    <i> AND OPERATED ARSENAL.</i>      

942
00:41:33,890 --> 00:41:36,224
       <i> KRIS LEINICKE IS</i>        
  <i> THE CURATOR OF THE MUSEUM,</i>   

943
00:41:36,292 --> 00:41:38,493
         <i> WHICH HOUSES</i>          
   <i> AN EXTENSIVE COLLECTION</i>     

944
00:41:38,561 --> 00:41:40,428
<i> OF HISTORIC MILITARY WEAPONS.</i>  

945
00:41:40,497 --> 00:41:43,064
THIS IS THE DEVICE              
I WANTED TO SHOW YOU.           

946
00:41:43,133 --> 00:41:44,265
                           OKAY.

947
00:41:44,334 --> 00:41:45,299
                        WOW.    

948
00:41:45,368 --> 00:41:46,801
WHAT DO YOU THINK               
IT COULD BE?                    

949
00:41:46,870 --> 00:41:49,837
    IT LOOKS TO ME LIKE IT MIGHT
    BE A CIVIL-WAR TORPEDO.     

950
00:41:49,906 --> 00:41:51,172
    TORPEDO?                    

951
00:41:51,241 --> 00:41:52,774
  <i> KRIS EXPLAINS THAT TODAY,</i>    

952
00:41:52,842 --> 00:41:54,942
       <i> TORPEDO IS KNOWN</i>        
   <i> AS AN UNDERWATER WEAPON</i>     

953
00:41:55,011 --> 00:41:56,878
  <i> LAUNCHED FROM A SUBMARINE</i>    
         <i> OR WARSHIP,</i>           

954
00:41:56,946 --> 00:41:59,647
       <i> BUT IT ONCE HAD</i>         
  <i> A MUCH BROADER DEFINITION.</i>   

955
00:41:59,716 --> 00:42:01,349
     BEFORE THE FIRST WORLD WAR,

956
00:42:01,418 --> 00:42:06,154
      A TORPEDO MEANT ANY HIDDEN
      EXPLOSIVE OR LAND MINE.   

957
00:42:06,222 --> 00:42:09,357
<i> KRIS SAYS THAT PERCUSSION CAPS,</i>
  <i> WHICH FIT OVER THE NIPPLES</i>   

958
00:42:09,426 --> 00:42:12,160
    <i> AND PRODUCE THE SPARKS</i>     
 <i> THAT IGNITED THE GUNPOWDER,</i>   

959
00:42:12,228 --> 00:42:14,595
 <i> WERE A CIVIL-WAR TECHNOLOGY.</i>  

960
00:42:14,664 --> 00:42:16,964
SO IS THIS                      
A MILITARY DEVICE, THEN?        

961
00:42:17,033 --> 00:42:20,635
        I DON'T THINK IT IS,    
        BECAUSE IT'S NOT MARKED,

962
00:42:20,703 --> 00:42:22,937
          AND A LOT OF MILITARY 
          EQUIPMENT AT THAT TIME

963
00:42:23,006 --> 00:42:24,405
              DID HAVE MARKINGS.

964
00:42:24,474 --> 00:42:28,075
        THE OTHER THING IS THAT 
        THE COLLAR ON THE NIPPLE

965
00:42:28,144 --> 00:42:31,312
   IS DIFFERENT THAN ON MILITARY
   WEAPONS OF THAT TIME PERIOD. 

966
00:42:31,381 --> 00:42:32,814
                LET ME SHOW YOU.

967
00:42:32,882 --> 00:42:34,782
              WE HAVE HERE      
              A CIVIL-WAR WEAPON

968
00:42:34,851 --> 00:42:36,851
           THAT WAS MADE        
           AT WATERTOWN ARSENAL,

969
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:39,086
     AND YOU CAN SEE            
     THAT THIS ITEM THAT WE HAVE

970
00:42:39,155 --> 00:42:41,255
            HAS A SQRE COLLAR.  

971
00:42:41,324 --> 00:42:45,726
 <i> IT'S A TINY DETAIL, BUT KRIS</i>  
<i> EXPLAINS THAT THE U.S. MILITARY</i>

972
00:42:45,795 --> 00:42:50,164
<i> ROUTINELY USED SQUARE COLLARS</i>  
    <i> ON PERCUSSION WEAPONS.</i>     

973
00:42:50,233 --> 00:42:52,433
  <i> OUR COLLAR IS RECTANGULAR.</i>   

974
00:42:52,502 --> 00:42:54,168
   <i> I ASK KRIS IF SHE THINKS</i>    

975
00:42:54,237 --> 00:42:56,370
       <i> THERE'S ANYTHING</i>        
       <i> TO WARREN'S IDEA</i>        

976
00:42:56,439 --> 00:42:59,240
 <i> THAT THE DEVICE WAS DESIGNED</i>  
   <i> TO DETER GRAVE ROBBERS.</i>     

977
00:42:59,309 --> 00:43:02,410
THAT'S REALLY INTERESTING, BUT  
I'VE NEVER HEARD OF THAT BEFORE.

978
00:43:02,478 --> 00:43:04,779
 <i> AND IF THIS HAD BEEN BURIED,</i>  

979
00:43:04,848 --> 00:43:07,215
<i> KRIS SPOTS WHAT APPEARS TO BE</i>  
         <i> A FATAL FLAW</i>          

980
00:43:07,283 --> 00:43:09,083
        <i> IN THE DESIGN</i>          
       <i> OF OUR TORPEDO.</i>         

981
00:43:09,152 --> 00:43:12,019
           THE OTHER PROBLEM IS,
           ONCE YOU BURIED IT,  

982
00:43:12,088 --> 00:43:15,356
   YOU'D HAVE DIRT IN HERE,     
   AND THEN HOW WOULD THE HAMMER

983
00:43:15,425 --> 00:43:18,426
          HIT THE PERCUSSION CAP
          THAT'S ON THE NIPPLE  

984
00:43:18,494 --> 00:43:20,494
        TO CREATE THE EXPLOSION?

985
00:43:20,563 --> 00:43:22,630
            BUT IT'S DEFINITELY 
            PROFESSIONALLY MADE,

986
00:43:22,699 --> 00:43:25,199
     SO IT HAS TO HAVE SOME KIND
     OF PRACTICAL USE.          

987
00:43:30,707 --> 00:43:33,441
    YOU KNOW, IF OUR DEVICE     
       REALLY WAS MEANT         

988
00:43:33,509 --> 00:43:35,176
    TO DETER GRAVE ROBBERS,     

989
00:43:35,245 --> 00:43:38,479
THERE'S GOTO BE SOME ACCOUNT    
  OF ONE OF THESE GOING OFF.    

990
00:43:40,850 --> 00:43:42,783
    <i> I TRY SEARCHING ONLINE</i>     

991
00:43:42,852 --> 00:43:46,120
    <i> TO SEE WHAT I CAN FIND</i>     
     <i> ABOUT GRAVE ALARMS.</i>       

992
00:43:46,189 --> 00:43:49,156
   <i> I DON'T TURN ANYTHING UP</i>    
<i> SEARCHING UNDER GRAVE ALARMS,</i>  

993
00:43:49,225 --> 00:43:53,194
      <i> BUT GRAVE TORPEDO,</i>       
 <i> WHICH IS THE TERM KRIS USED,</i>  

994
00:43:53,263 --> 00:43:56,063
    <i> RETURNS A CURIOUS HIT.</i>     

995
00:43:56,132 --> 00:43:58,966
    OKAY, HERE'S AN ARTICLE     
  FROM THE<i> RICHWOOD GAZETTE,</i>    

996
00:43:59,035 --> 00:44:01,269
         1881 IN OHIO:          

997
00:44:01,337 --> 00:44:03,237
    "GRAVE ROBBER KILLED."      

998
00:44:03,306 --> 00:44:06,107
   "THREE MEN WHO ATTEMPTED     
        TO ROB A GRAVE          

999
00:44:06,175 --> 00:44:09,076
          "NEAR GANN,           
     IN KNOX COUNTY, OHIO,      

1000
00:44:09,145 --> 00:44:11,579
"MET WITH A HORRIBLE OBSTACLE.  

1001
00:44:11,648 --> 00:44:14,482
   WHEN NEARING THE COFFIN,     
    THEY STRUCK A TORPEDO."     

1002
00:44:14,550 --> 00:44:17,251
        SO THESE THINGS         
       REALLY DID EXIST.        

1003
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:20,821
    <i> ONE OF THESE DEVICES,</i>      
      <i> PATENTED IN 1881,</i>        

1004
00:44:20,890 --> 00:44:22,957
        <i> SOUNDS SIMILAR</i>         
           <i> TO OURS.</i>            

1005
00:44:23,026 --> 00:44:26,160
         THOMAS HOWELL          
     OF CIRCLEVILLE, OHIO,      

1006
00:44:26,229 --> 00:44:28,829
           PATENTED             
      AN EXPLODING SHELL        

1007
00:44:28,898 --> 00:44:31,732
        THAT WAS BURIED         
     RIGHT ABOVE A COFFIN.      

1008
00:44:31,801 --> 00:44:34,068
     AND IF ROBBERS TRIED       
     TO DIG UP THE COFFIN,      

1009
00:44:34,137 --> 00:44:35,770
   "THE SHELL WOULD EXPLODE,    

1010
00:44:35,838 --> 00:44:38,739
      INJURING OR KILLING       
         THE THIEVES."          

1011
00:44:38,808 --> 00:44:42,009
<i> IT APPEARS THAT IN THESE CASES,</i>
 <i> AT LEAST, THE GRAVE ROBBERS</i>   

1012
00:44:42,078 --> 00:44:44,845
<i> WEREN'T TRYING TO SWIPE JEWELRY</i>
     <i> AND OTHER VALUABLES,</i>      

1013
00:44:44,914 --> 00:44:47,214
       <i> THEY WERE TRYING</i>        
       <i> TO STEAL BODIES.</i>        

1014
00:44:47,283 --> 00:44:52,153
IT SAYS THAT DURING THE 1800s,  
MEDICAL SCHOOLS STOLE CADAVERS  

1015
00:44:52,221 --> 00:44:56,090
 TO DEMONSTRATE GROSS ANATOMY   
        TO THE STUDENTS         

1016
00:44:56,159 --> 00:45:00,161
AND THAT THIS WAS PARTICULARLY  
      A PROBLEM IN OHIO.        

1017
00:45:05,134 --> 00:45:08,169
<i> SCOTT GAMPHER IS THE DIRECTOR</i>  
    <i> OF HISTORY COLLECTIONS</i>     

1018
00:45:08,237 --> 00:45:11,105
<i> AT THE CINCINNATI MUSEUM CENTER</i>
      <i> AT UNION TERMINAL.</i>       

1019
00:45:11,174 --> 00:45:13,741
       <i> HE'S NEVER SEEN</i>         
  <i> ANYTHING LIKE OUR DEVICE,</i>    

1020
00:45:13,810 --> 00:45:17,378
<i> BUT HE UNDERSTANDS THE HISTORIC</i>
<i> NEED TO PREVENT BODY SNATCHING.</i>

1021
00:45:17,447 --> 00:45:19,046
THERE WERE A LOT                
OF DISSECTIONS                  

1022
00:45:19,115 --> 00:45:21,015
THAT WERE TAKING PLACE          
IN THESE MEDICAL COLLEGES,      

1023
00:45:21,084 --> 00:45:23,117
AND THUS A NEED                 
FOR A LOT OF CADAVERS.          

1024
00:45:23,186 --> 00:45:26,120
    <i> BETWEEN 1865 AND 1890,</i>     

1025
00:45:26,189 --> 00:45:30,057
<i> THE NUMBER OF MEDICAL SCHOOLS</i>  
 <i> IN THE U.S. ALMOST DOUBLED.</i>   

1026
00:45:30,126 --> 00:45:33,194
<i> CINCINNATI-AREA MEDICAL SCHOOLS</i>
   <i> COMPETED WITH EACH OTHER</i>    

1027
00:45:33,262 --> 00:45:35,963
<i> TO OFFER PRACTICAL EXPERIENCE</i>  
         <i> TO STUDENTS.</i>          

1028
00:45:36,032 --> 00:45:38,966
     <i> BUT BODIES WERE NOT</i>       
       <i> EASY TO COME BY:</i>        

1029
00:45:39,035 --> 00:45:41,435
     <i> THE CHURCH OBJECTED,</i>      
       <i> AND MANY STATES</i>         

1030
00:45:41,504 --> 00:45:44,238
  <i> ONLY PERMITTED THE BODIES</i>    
    <i> OF EXECUTED CRIMINALS</i>      

1031
00:45:44,307 --> 00:45:46,173
  <i> TO BE USED FOR DISSECTION.</i>   

1032
00:45:46,242 --> 00:45:48,509
AND SO, REALLY, THE ONLY AVENUE 
FOR THESE SCHOOLS               

1033
00:45:48,578 --> 00:45:51,078
TO OBTAIN CADAVERS              
WAS THROUGH THE BLACK MARKET.   

1034
00:45:51,147 --> 00:45:53,747
IN OTHER WORDS, BY DOING        
BUSINESS WITH GRAVE ROBBERS.    

1035
00:45:53,816 --> 00:45:57,718
 <i> IN THE 1870s, PUBLIC CONCERN</i>  
     <i> ABOUT BODY SNATCHING</i>      

1036
00:45:57,787 --> 00:46:00,387
     <i> WAS AT A FEVER PITCH</i>      
    <i> IN OHIO IN PARTICULAR</i>      

1037
00:46:00,456 --> 00:46:02,756
          <i> BECAUSE OF</i>           
    <i> A NOTORIOUS INCIDENT.</i>      

1038
00:46:02,825 --> 00:46:10,965
         <i> THE BODY OF</i>           
     <i> JOHN SCOTT HARRISON,</i>      

1039
00:46:11,033 --> 00:46:14,502
  <i> FATHER OF FUTURE PRESIDENT</i>   
      <i> BENJAMINM A ROPE</i>         

1040
00:46:14,570 --> 00:46:17,738
      <i> DOWN A DARK SHAFT</i>        
<i> AT THE MEDICAL COLLEGE OF OHIO,</i>

1041
00:46:17,807 --> 00:46:20,307
 <i> PROVOKING ENORMOUS OUTRAGE.</i>   

1042
00:46:20,376 --> 00:46:22,076
IT WAS PARTICULARLY BAD         

1043
00:46:22,144 --> 00:46:24,678
BECAUSE MEASURES HAD BEEN TAKEN 
BY THE HARRISON FAMILY          

1044
00:46:24,747 --> 00:46:26,981
TO PREVENT THIS VERY THING      
FROM HAPPENING.                 

1045
00:46:27,049 --> 00:46:28,516
        <i> SCOTT SHOWS ME</i>         
          <i> AN ARTICLE</i>           

1046
00:46:28,584 --> 00:46:30,451
     <i> FROM THE</i> CINCINNATI       
       DAILY COMMERCIAL         

1047
00:46:30,520 --> 00:46:34,822
  <i> WRITTEN IN 1878 JUST AFTER</i>   
 <i> HARRISON'S BODY WAS STOLEN.</i>   

1048
00:46:34,891 --> 00:46:38,726
    "IF CEMENTED WALLS CAREFULLY
    AND SKILLFULLY CONSTRUCTED, 

1049
00:46:38,794 --> 00:46:42,563
"AND VAST WEIGHTS, REQUIRING THE
STRENGTH OF MANY MEN TO LIFT,   

1050
00:46:42,632 --> 00:46:45,065
"AND HIRED AND PRE-PAID WATCHMEN

1051
00:46:45,134 --> 00:46:47,968
     "COULD NOT SAVE THEIR LOVED
     AND HONORED PARENT'S GRAVE 

1052
00:46:48,037 --> 00:46:51,338
  FROM DESECRATION AND DISHONOR,
  WHAT COULD?"                  

1053
00:46:51,407 --> 00:46:52,606
            WOW.                

1054
00:46:52,675 --> 00:46:54,041
AND I THINK THAT'S              
ONE OF THE THINGS               

1055
00:46:54,110 --> 00:46:55,442
THAT SHOCKED THE PUBLIC         
SO MUCH:                        

1056
00:46:55,511 --> 00:46:57,044
"WELL, IF IT COULD HAPPEN       
TO THE HARRISONS,               

1057
00:46:57,113 --> 00:46:59,079
IT COULD HAPPEN                 
TO ANYBODY."                    

1058
00:46:59,148 --> 00:47:01,615
        <i> THE PUBLIC HAD</i>         
       <i> RUN OUT OF WAYS</i>         

1059
00:47:01,684 --> 00:47:04,752
          <i> TO SECURE</i>            
   <i> THEIR LOVED ONE'S GRAVE,</i>    

1060
00:47:04,820 --> 00:47:08,789
   <i> SO THEY TURNED TO DEADLY</i>    
 <i> EXPLOSIVES AS A LAST RESORT.</i>  

1061
00:47:08,858 --> 00:47:12,092
   <i> BUT IS OUR DEVICE REALLY</i>    
   <i> ONE OF THESE TORPEDOES?</i>     

1062
00:47:12,161 --> 00:47:13,560
    <i> WITHOUT A MAKER'S MARK</i>     

1063
00:47:13,629 --> 00:47:16,830
    <i> OR A CLEAR EXPLANATION</i>     
 <i> FOR HOW IT MIGHT'VE WORKED,</i>   

1064
00:47:16,899 --> 00:47:19,233
      <i> I'M STILL NOT SURE</i>       
        <i> WHAT WE HAVE.</i>          

1065
00:47:23,673 --> 00:47:26,173
   <i> SCOTT PUT ME IN CONTACT</i>     
     <i> WITH PAUL MAYBERRY,</i>       

1066
00:47:26,242 --> 00:47:29,043
     <i> THE LOCAL HISTORIAN</i>       
  <i> OF PICKAWAY COUNTY, OHIO.</i>    

1067
00:47:29,111 --> 00:47:31,312
      <i> PICKAWAY INCLUDES</i>        
   <i> THE TOWN OF CIRCLEVILLE,</i>    

1068
00:47:31,380 --> 00:47:35,215
     <i> WHERE THOMAS HOWELL</i>       
    <i> INVENTED HIS TORPEDO.</i>      

1069
00:47:35,284 --> 00:47:37,951
              MY RESEARCH LED ME
              TO CIRCLEVILLE    

1070
00:47:38,020 --> 00:47:39,620
         BECAUSE OF THIS OBJECT.

1071
00:47:39,689 --> 00:47:42,256
       DO YOU KNOW WHAT THIS IS?

1072
00:47:42,325 --> 00:47:44,925
WELL, THAT'S REALLY SOMETHING.  

1073
00:47:44,994 --> 00:47:47,027
     <i> PAUL HAS NEVER SEEN</i>       
     <i> ONE OF THESE BEFORE,</i>      

1074
00:47:47,096 --> 00:47:48,862
 <i> BUT HE SAYS GRAVE TORPEDOES</i>   

1075
00:47:48,931 --> 00:47:50,864
     <i> HAVE A LONG HISTORY</i>       
        <i> IN THE REGION.</i>         

1076
00:47:50,933 --> 00:47:54,034
OUR LOCAL CEMETERY              
ABOLISHED THE USE OF THEM,      

1077
00:47:54,103 --> 00:47:58,439
I THINK, IN 1890 BECAUSE IT WAS 
TOO MUCH OF A DANGER            

1078
00:47:58,507 --> 00:48:01,508
TO THE PEOPLE WHO WERE          
WORKING IN THE CEMETERY.        

1079
00:48:01,577 --> 00:48:04,611
      SUPPOSEDLY THERE WAS A GUY
      NAMED THOMAS HOWELL       

1080
00:48:04,680 --> 00:48:08,682
   WHO LIVED HERE IN CIRCLEVILLE
   WHO MADE DEVICES LIKE THIS.  

1081
00:48:08,751 --> 00:48:10,117
             HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
             OF HOWELL?         

1082
00:48:10,186 --> 00:48:11,251
    YES, I HAVE.                

1083
00:48:11,320 --> 00:48:13,487
I'VE DONE SOME RESEARCH         
ON THOMAS HOWELL.               

1084
00:48:13,556 --> 00:48:17,157
HE WAS A WATCH MAKER AND TIMES  
GOT A LITTLE TOUGH FOR HIM,     

1085
00:48:17,226 --> 00:48:20,861
AND HE DECIDED TO RESOLVE       
SOME OF THE PROBLEMS            

1086
00:48:20,930 --> 00:48:23,230
WE HAD WITH GRAVE ROBBING.      

1087
00:48:23,299 --> 00:48:26,100
   <i> PAUL ASSEMBLED A NUMBER</i>     
 <i> OF LOCAL ARTICLES ON HOWELL</i>   

1088
00:48:26,168 --> 00:48:28,268
        <i> THAT HE COPIED</i>         
     <i> FROM OLD NEWSPAPERS.</i>      

1089
00:48:28,337 --> 00:48:31,238
THIS IS SOME OF THE ADVERTISING 
THAT HE DID.                    

1090
00:48:31,307 --> 00:48:33,707
         SO IT LOOKS LIKE       
         IT'S FROM THE NEWSPAPER

1091
00:48:33,776 --> 00:48:36,477
             FROM JULY 11, 1879.

1092
00:48:36,545 --> 00:48:38,746
       THE AD SAYS,             
       "SLEEP WELL, SWEET ANGEL.

1093
00:48:38,814 --> 00:48:42,282
         "LET NO FEARS OF GHOULS
         DISTURB THY REST,      

1094
00:48:42,351 --> 00:48:46,453
    "FOR ABOVE THY SHROUDED FORM
    LIES A TORPEDO,             

1095
00:48:46,522 --> 00:48:49,223
       "READY TO MAKE MINCE-MEAT
       OF ANYONE                

1096
00:48:49,291 --> 00:48:52,059
      WHO ATTEMPTS TO CONVEY YOU
      TO THE PICKLING VAT."     

1097
00:48:52,128 --> 00:48:54,461
        WOW, THAT IS INCREDIBLE!

1098
00:48:54,530 --> 00:48:57,397
     I MEAN, THAT'S PRETTY GOOD 
     DIRECT MARKETING, ISN'T IT?

1099
00:48:57,466 --> 00:48:58,799
        IT IS.                  

1100
00:48:58,868 --> 00:49:00,901
 <i> BUT THE PICTURE OF HOWELL'S</i>   
        <i> GRAVE TORPEDO</i>          

1101
00:49:00,970 --> 00:49:03,003
   <i> LOOKS NOTHING LIKE OURS.</i>    

1102
00:49:03,072 --> 00:49:05,506
          <i> DO WE HAVE</i>           
       <i> A GRAVE TORPEDO?</i>        

1103
00:49:05,574 --> 00:49:07,541
<i> AND HOW WOULD IT HAVE WORKED?</i>  

1104
00:49:07,610 --> 00:49:09,810
              HERE'S THE PROBLEM
              THAT I HAVE.      

1105
00:49:09,879 --> 00:49:13,313
    IF YOU SET THIS THING       
    AND YOU PUT IT INTO A GRAVE,

1106
00:49:13,382 --> 00:49:16,216
       WHAT'S TO PREVENT IT FROM
       EXPLODING IN YOUR FACE?  

1107
00:49:16,285 --> 00:49:18,619
WELL, THIS IS                   
AN INGENIOUS DEVICE.            

1108
00:49:18,687 --> 00:49:20,554
   <i> WHAT PAUL SHOWS ME NEXT</i>     

1109
00:49:20,623 --> 00:49:23,490
  <i> GIVES ME THE ANSWER I NEED</i>   
         <i> FOR WARREN.</i>           

1110
00:49:23,559 --> 00:49:26,627
WHEN YOU FIRST SHOWED ME        
THIS THING                      

1111
00:49:26,695 --> 00:49:29,129
AND YOU THOUGHT IT WAS          
SOME SORT OF A GRAVE ALARM,     

1112
00:49:29,198 --> 00:49:31,431
I SAID, "COME ON,               
THIS GUY'S CRAZY!               

1113
00:49:31,500 --> 00:49:33,300
IT COULDN'T BE                  
A GRAVE ALARM."                 

1114
00:49:33,369 --> 00:49:35,969
BUT AS I GOT INTO               
THE INVESTIGATION,              

1115
00:49:36,038 --> 00:49:40,140
I DISCOVERED THAT               
THIS IS NOT SO MUCH AN ALARM    

1116
00:49:40,209 --> 00:49:42,276
AS IT IS A DEADLY WEAPON.       

1117
00:49:42,344 --> 00:49:43,944
                 OH, YEAH?      

1118
00:49:44,013 --> 00:49:46,613
         <i> I TELL HENRY</i>          
 <i> THAT HIS DEVICE WAS DESIGNED</i>  

1119
00:49:46,682 --> 00:49:49,850
  <i> TO DETER THIEVES STEALING</i>    
    <i> BODIES, NOT VALUABLES.</i>     

1120
00:49:49,919 --> 00:49:52,553
      WELL, THE GUYS I TALKED TO
      WERE HALF RIGHT, ANYWAY.  

1121
00:49:52,621 --> 00:49:54,288
HERE'S THE THING                
I COULDN'T FIGURE OUT:          

1122
00:49:54,356 --> 00:49:57,591
HOW COULD YOU PUT THIS          
INTO A GRAVE,                   

1123
00:49:57,660 --> 00:50:01,595
SET THE TRIGGERS,               
AND FILL THE GRAVE UP           

1124
00:50:01,664 --> 00:50:03,630
WITHOUT BLOWING                 
YOUR HEAD OFF?                  

1125
00:50:03,699 --> 00:50:06,533
    YOU GOT ME IN SUSPENSE HERE!

1126
00:50:06,602 --> 00:50:10,304
THOMAS HOWELL WAS SO SUCCESSFUL 
WITH HIS FIRST GRAVE TORPEDO    

1127
00:50:10,372 --> 00:50:12,606
THAT HE DESIGNED                
ANOTHER ONE,                    

1128
00:50:12,675 --> 00:50:14,608
AND I HAVE A PATENT             
FOR THAT ONE HERE.              

1129
00:50:14,677 --> 00:50:16,376
                     NO, REALLY?

1130
00:50:16,445 --> 00:50:20,414
             "GRAVE TORPEDO,    
             DECEMBER 20, 1881."

1131
00:50:20,482 --> 00:50:23,283
    <i> THE OLD PATENT PAPERS</i>      
   <i> SHOW A CURIOUS PARABOLA,</i>    

1132
00:50:23,352 --> 00:50:25,919
     <i> OR ARC, OVER THE TOP</i>      
       <i> OF OUR TORPEDO,</i>         

1133
00:50:25,988 --> 00:50:30,324
<i> AND SUDDENLY I UNDERSTAND HOW</i>  
<i> OUR DEVICE IS SUPPOSED TO WORK.</i>

1134
00:50:30,392 --> 00:50:32,125
        WHAT'S MISSING FROM HERE

1135
00:50:32,194 --> 00:50:35,262
          IS A THIN METAL SHIELD
          THAT FIT OVER THIS    

1136
00:50:35,331 --> 00:50:37,331
                THAT HAD A HOLE 
                IN THE MIDDLE...

1137
00:50:37,399 --> 00:50:38,799
RIGHT.                          

1138
00:50:38,867 --> 00:50:41,201
 THAT ACCORDING TO THE PATENT   
 PAPERS, YOU'D TAKE A LONG TUBE,

1139
00:50:41,270 --> 00:50:43,971
     LIKE A STANDPIPE, YOU'D    
     PUT A FUNNEL UP AT THE TOP,

1140
00:50:44,039 --> 00:50:45,973
            AFTER THIS IS BURIED
            IN THE GRAVE...     

1141
00:50:46,041 --> 00:50:47,240
CORRECT.                        

1142
00:50:47,309 --> 00:50:49,810
  AND YOU'D FILL THIS CHAMBER UP
  WITH GUNPOWDER.               

1143
00:50:49,878 --> 00:50:52,079
         THEN ONCE THE CHAMBER'S
         FILLED UP,             

1144
00:50:52,147 --> 00:50:55,215
 YOU'D DROP A CORK DOWN         
 THE STANDPIPE, OR SOME STOPPER.

1145
00:50:55,284 --> 00:50:59,686
  <i> WHEN THE TRIPWIRES SECURED</i>   
        <i> TO THE COLLAR</i>          

1146
00:50:59,755 --> 00:51:02,456
        <i> ARE DISTURBED</i>          
     <i> BY A GRAVE ROBBER...</i>      

1147
00:51:02,524 --> 00:51:06,560
         THE THING GOES KA-BOOM!

1148
00:51:06,628 --> 00:51:12,065
         WOW, I WOULD SAY       
         THAT'S THE SAME DEVICE.

1149
00:51:12,134 --> 00:51:15,769
      <i> BECAUSE HIS DEVICE</i>       
    <i> HAS NO MARKINGS ON IT</i>      

1150
00:51:15,838 --> 00:51:18,638
     <i> AND BECAUSE IT'S NOT</i>      
       <i> AN EXACT MATCH,</i>         

1151
00:51:18,707 --> 00:51:20,807
  <i> HENRY MAY HAVE A PROTOTYPE</i>   

1152
00:51:20,876 --> 00:51:23,443
     <i> OF HOWELL'S PATENTED</i>      
        <i> GRAVE TORPEDO.</i>         

1153
00:51:23,512 --> 00:51:27,748
              IT'S SO CLOSE THAT
              IT'S GOT TO BE IT.

1154
00:51:27,816 --> 00:51:29,249
                 IT'S GOT TO BE.

1155
00:51:29,318 --> 00:51:31,318
              YOU GUYS REALLY   
              DID A JOB ON THIS.

1156
00:51:31,387 --> 00:51:32,853
          THIS IS WORTH KNOWING.

1157
00:51:32,921 --> 00:51:35,255
              THIS IS -- I MEAN,
              THIS IS HISTORY.  

1158
00:51:35,324 --> 00:51:37,190
WELL, THIS HAS BEEN             
A GREAT INVESTIGATION,          

1159
00:51:37,259 --> 00:51:39,059
AND I REALLY APPRECIATE YOU     
BRINGING THIS TO ME.            

1160
00:51:39,128 --> 00:51:40,560
               YOU'RE RIGHT     
               ON THE BALL, WES.

1161
00:51:40,629 --> 00:51:42,763
             PUT 'ER THERE, PAL.

1162
00:51:42,831 --> 00:51:48,135
  <i> IN 1881, THE YEAR HOWELL'S</i>   
 <i> GRAVE TORPEDO WAS PATENTED,</i>   

1163
00:51:48,203 --> 00:51:50,470
         <i> OHIO ENACTED</i>          
       <i> THE ANATOMY LAW.</i>        

1164
00:51:50,539 --> 00:51:53,440
 <i> IT PERMITTED MEDICAL SCHOOLS</i>  
   <i> TO USE UNCLAIMED BODIES</i>     

1165
00:51:53,509 --> 00:51:55,408
  <i> FROM PUBLIC INSTITUTIONS.</i>    

1166
00:51:55,477 --> 00:51:57,110
 <i> BY THE TURN OF THE CENTURY,</i>   

1167
00:51:57,179 --> 00:52:00,881
     <i> BODY SNATCHING CASES</i>      
 <i> HAD SIGNIFICANTLY DECLINED.</i>   

1168
00:52:00,949 --> 00:52:03,817
     <i> CADAVER STORAGE AND</i>       
    <i> PRESERVATION IMPROVED,</i>     

1169
00:52:03,886 --> 00:52:06,620
       <i> ALLOWING SCHOOLS</i>        
    <i> TO ACCUMULATE BODIES,</i>      

1170
00:52:06,688 --> 00:52:09,489
  <i> AND THE NEED FOR STEALING</i>    
     <i> FRESH HUMAN CORPSES</i>       

1171
00:52:09,558 --> 00:52:11,525
   <i> WAS A THING OF THE PAST.</i>    

1172
00:52:15,430 --> 00:52:19,733
EVEN PRESIDENTIAL BURIAL SITES  
 WERE PREY FOR GRAVE ROBBERS.   

1173
00:52:19,802 --> 00:52:23,937
      ELEVEN YEARS AFTER        
ABRAHAM LINCOLN'S ASSASSINATION,

1174
00:52:24,006 --> 00:52:28,341
A CRIMINAL GANG HATCHED A PLOT  
     TO RANSOM HIS CORPSE.      

1175
00:52:28,410 --> 00:52:30,677
     THEY WANTED $200,000       

1176
00:52:30,746 --> 00:52:33,446
        AND THE RELEASE         
   OF AN IMPRISONED COHORT.     

1177
00:52:33,515 --> 00:52:38,785
  ON ELECTION NIGHT 1876, THE   
 THIEVES RAIDED LINCOLN'S TOMB  

1178
00:52:38,854 --> 00:52:40,954
   IN SPRINGFIELD, ILLINOIS.    

1179
00:52:41,023 --> 00:52:43,657
       BUT THE 500-POUND        
     CEDAR AND LEAD COFFIN      

1180
00:52:43,725 --> 00:52:45,425
    WAS TOO HEAVY TO MOVE.      

1181
00:52:45,494 --> 00:52:48,161
TIPPED-OFF SECRET SERVICE AGENTS
        ARRIVED IN TIME         

1182
00:52:48,230 --> 00:52:52,599
     TO CATCH THE WOULD-BE      
   GRAVE ROBBERS IN THE ACT.    

1183
00:52:52,668 --> 00:52:54,834
 AFTER THE ATTEMPTED ROBBERY,   

1184
00:52:54,903 --> 00:52:57,304
     THE NATIONAL LINCOLN       
       MONUMENT SOCIETY         

1185
00:52:57,372 --> 00:53:01,875
SECRETLY MOVED LINCOLN'S CORPSE 
 TO ANOTHER PART OF THE TOMB.   

1186
00:53:01,944 --> 00:53:04,444
  FOR YEARS, THE PUBLIC PAID    
        THEIR RESPECTS          

1187
00:53:04,513 --> 00:53:07,147
   TO AN EMPTY SARCOPHAGUS.     

1188
00:53:07,216 --> 00:53:11,685
BEFORE LINCOLN'S BODY WAS LAID  
  TO ITS FINAL RESTING PLACE,   

1189
00:53:11,753 --> 00:53:14,287
        IT WAS EXHUMED          
       AND CHECKED TWICE        

1190
00:53:14,356 --> 00:53:17,657
    TO MAKE SURE THE CORPSE     
       WAS STILL THERE.         

1191
00:53:17,726 --> 00:53:19,426
   AS A LAST SAFETY MEASURE,    

1192
00:53:19,494 --> 00:53:22,862
      IN 1901, PRESIDENT        
   AND MRS. LINCOLN'S BODIES    

1193
00:53:22,931 --> 00:53:24,864
     WERE ENCASED IN LEAD.      

1194
00:53:24,933 --> 00:53:27,000
   THEIR COFFINS WERE CAGED     
           IN STEEL             

1195
00:53:27,069 --> 00:53:29,970
      AND BURIED BENEATH        
      10 FEET OF CEMENT,        

1196
00:53:30,038 --> 00:53:34,941
ENSURING THAT LINCOLN WOULD STAY
    IN SPRINGFIELD FOREVER.     

